text:
📖 what is drug addiction? 🤔
.
“addiction is defined as a chronic, relapsing disorder characterized by compulsive drug seeking and use despite adverse consequences. .
it is considered a brain disorder, because it involves functional changes to brain circuits involved in reward, stress, and self-control, and those changes may last a long time after a person has stopped taking drugs.
.
addiction is a lot like other diseases, such as heart disease. both disrupt the normal, healthy functioning of an organ in the body, both have serious harmful effects, and both are, in many cases, preventable and treatable. if left untreated, they can last a lifetime and may lead to death.”
.
(source: https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/drugs-brains-behavior-science-addiction/drug-misuse-addiction).
.
how can we progress as a society and move towards harm reductive, compassionate interventions if those addicted to substances (who are often traumatised/ mentally vulnerable people) are vilified and incarcerated by our legal and judicial systems?. .
there is a reason why people become addicted to substances. it’s a bio-medical issue, it’s a matter of co-morbidity and dual-diagnosis, which are multifaceted complexities of a human beings holistic predicament.
.
we need to start the conversation and start wiping away preconditioned conventions of what we believe addiction really is.
.
this is one of australia’s biggest barriers and we as a collective can challenge the stigma and negative preconceptions. it’s a matter of perception.. and we need to hear your stories to wipe away the collective myths which our society has been constantly telling us 🙌.
.
humans have created barriers, and humans can bring them back down 🙏✨☮️.
.
come be on this journey together! please help us by sharing this cause with others so we can grow and prosper together 🌿💞

text:
moni; the girl who got out starring mojy show who also wrote and produced the short film, and directed by tunde abiola, displays the narrative of a young woman succumbed to an unfortunate circumstance. a circumstance that occurs all too frequently; really an antique yet unceasing crisis. this crisis is one that regards 1 out of every 6 female children, girls, and adult women or for the power of perspective, an estimated 17.7 million female children, teenage girls and women are victims of attempted or completed rape, here in the united states. what about in our motherland africa?...though there are very few to almost no reliable sources for the continent of africa as a whole…several studies have repeated that on average, 1 in 4 female children, teenage girls and women have experienced the gruesome act of completed rape…and those are only the ones that were reported. both myself writing this and you as the reader know all too well, that the unreported skews these numbers! the short story of moni is another clear cut, open book example of the crux so many are dutifully speaking out against. awareness! it's a story i foresee will inspire the unspoken, the afraid, those surrounded by shame and taboo to maybe speak. whether its to speak out against their abusers or the abuser of a family member and if they are not ready to say #metoo it may encourage entering the fight of increased awareness and bringing justice to open victims. moni forces you to think about the disconnect between sexual / social boundaries and ones own moral compass and depending on whose watching, it may trigger certain feelings towards society especially the members of society you thought would out them for you, but kept quiet as well! 
moni, a must watch! --natasha ewa, licensed clinical social worker

text:
every day she becomes a bit more “my daughter”... we didn’t find out her gender ahead of time. though deep down i just knew we were having a girl. i was secretly scared shitlesss... when i held her for the first time, i was scared shitless. 
what was i supposed to do with a baby girl. i have never been a girly girl, i have never been one to hang out with a ton of girls or do the girly things. i hated the mall. i did everything to go other places instead of the mall, even as a teenager. and god still trusted me with a girl. 😳 
i dressed her in the cutest of cute clothes, she sported the whale spout 🐳 like nobody’s business, she had the cutest & tiniest little girl voice and the most gorgeous eyes i’ve seen. she has the best eyes, just like my grams. 💕

i seen my mom in her... a lot. her looks, her little voice and her personality. 
i seen her daddy in her...those cheeks were definitely from the myers side! i promise. 
but..i never really seen me in her. she liked the girly things, but also trucks and helping in the garage. #balance she was a very calm and perfect baby. i am high energy and luke is the calm, more laid back one. she has one blue eye and one brown eye, mine are green. 
as she gets older, she is becoming a young lady i can see some of my side peeking out of. #finally 
she has my smile. my sass and love for life. she can be crazy and sing like no one hears her..that *may* be a bit of me too. 🤷‍♀️she enjoys sports and a good run, occasionally (though not as much as i wish she would join me). she loves adventure #metoo

i thank god every day for trusting me with this little girl. and each day i’m seeing more of myself in her personality, her looks and the things she enjoys doing. 
so blessed to have a daughter to love and navigate life with. 
always her mom but glad she enjoys spending time with me too. not too cool to hang with me yet... though i’m sure the time will come. 
#minime #motherdaughter #loveher #blessing #stopgrowingsofast #mylittlegirl #daddysgirl #mommyssidekick #mygirl
name: Zyia Active with DaniLynn

text:
if music could heal the soul , this is by far the one is literally the anthem of my soul that has helped bring immense healing .the words are so powerful, the proclamation couldn’t be closer to the truth “ i am no longer the slave to fear , i am a child of god” 
every word attached to “i am” is amplified a 1000x more in healing. so affirm that we are no longer slaves of fear we are children of god 
it marks a very sensitive time in my life but through the pain , the trials ; in all the mess god had a message. 
your purpose , our purpose is healing . we are healers . a healer cannot heal others unless they have healed themselves. but in order to heal, you need to experience the woes of pain. i will never know nor will i understand, but i kneel before your throne with the heart of a child trusting through it all you never left , through it all you were there , through it all we walked together 
#healing #selfhealing #godfirst #universalfaith #godismystrength #godismyhealer #refuge #source #nolongeraslavetofear #godfirstineverything #iamachildofgod #healers #metoo #metoomovement

text:
#rbg es un documental que nos permite conocer a ruth bader ginsburg, una mujer que ha sido de vital importancia en la lucha por la igualdad de derechos para las mujeres en norteamérica. 
en base a una sencilla narrativa, el documental tiene un enfoque lineal sobre la vida de ginsburg. ella reflexiona sobre una infancia que pasó deseando hacer las cosas "como lo hicieron los niños". varios amigos de la infancia, reporteros que durante mucho tiempo han cubierto el golpe de justicia, su propia familia, los biógrafos, los expertos en redes sociales que ayudaron a popularizar el apodo de "notorious rbg", incluso bill clinton, aparecen en pantalla para hablar sobre ruth.

la ligereza narrativa ayuda a que el film logre ser apreciado sin tecnicismos propios del derecho que impidan la fácil comprensión. sumar a ello la emoción que se siente al retratar la relación de pareja de ruth con su esposo, pilar importante en su vida y en todo el aspecto profesional. 
un importante documental para aprender mucho sobre una mujer aún valiosa para el mundo de hoy. en base a astucia, actitud, valentía y mucho amor, logró que su voz sea escuchada y sacar adelante muchas medidas en pro de la mujer norteamericana y, por qué no, del mundo. un ejemplo a tomar en cuenta para la coyuntura actual y que se sigue mitificando al pasar de los años. 
nominado a mejor documental en los #oscar2019. búsquenlo!

text:
7/100: global dystopias, junot diaz (editor) (2017)
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ this short collection from boston review was a mostly great collection of harrowing fiction. couple misses but some really great successes too. it felt like interspersing the stories and interviews/essays might have helped with unification, but maybe that’s just boston review’s format. also, junot diaz only writes the intro + interview questions, so the collection did not feel spoiled by his #metoo moment last year (although it certainly shapes the perception of the interview with margaret atwood in a very different light). #nonewbooks2019

text: my latest blog entry is posted (link in bio). “i had to step away for a minute in order to catch my breath. the upheaval of the storm swirled around me and beckoned, time slow down. debris settled. the rubble is recognizable but wholly unwelcome. there were days these past few weeks where i found myself engulfed by an all too familiar feeling, ‘i don’t want to be here - i don’t want to be alive.’ before i could stop it, my mind collaborated with my feelings, devising ways to make my suicide look like and accident. i lived my life wishing i could die while simultaneously pretending i didn’t feel that way - desperately trying to not feel that way. the tides of this truth washed in quickly and seemed to lift quite a bit once i told my counselor and members of my family. my counselor made me put in place a safety plan (a list of people & numbers to call) in case the suicidal feelings ever become unmanageable. i highly suggest a safety plan if you ever suffer suicidal thoughts.” “the construct of denial is interesting to me. it’s like living underwater. you don’t see or hear or move with accuracy. you try, but it just doesn’t happen. you know things happened and while the reality of it is elusive, the repercussions are apparent. and even when the effects are obvious, you still can’t fully grasp hold where it comes from and how to fix it; it just falls through every crack of your cupped hands” #timesup #metoo #sexualabusesurvivorsstories #sexualabuse www.teresabruce.blog
name: Illumine Freedom•Healing•Peace

text:
🌺 this retreat is like a beacon of light for the women out there who know that there are others like them, others who have heard the call to join in this collective conscious movement of empowering women.
✨
these women like you, are standing and starting to become aware that there is a pull, towards something bigger than us individually. the desire to become a part of something that is encouraging us to remember, reclaim and become who we are meant to be in this lifetime.
✨
the remembering we are experiencing is something that is calling and coaxing us back, something that is asking us to reclaim their power, these traditions, this knowledge, this wisdom that we know to be true and to bring it into the light!!
✨
it's time!!
✨
it's time to join together sisters!
✨
it's safe now!!
✨
time to weave and to bond.
✨
to become something stronger than the sum of us.
✨
this is a movement and this retreat is an opportunity for you to become and belong.
take the hand that we are offering...
🌺

text: check out my last post for more pics from the panel. this #metoo (@metoomvmt) with @hbo panel was next level! swipe to see the love (and a treat at the end from @terrycrews twitter) shout to @osopepatrisse for the connection. ✊🏽 men, we have some much work to do to continue to deconstruct our minds. as @taranajaneen said, this has to be the generation that break this culture!  remember men, because women of color have so many extra layers of oppression than men (including higher rates of sexual assault, pay disparity, maternal mortality, health care etc) doing the work of liberating women inevitably dismantles all forms of oppression that generally oppress men. you can liberate men by working to liberate women. but the opposite is not true. if you work to liberate only men, the other forms of oppression that are specific to women, still stay in tact. and you can apply that even further to other ever more intersectionally oppressed folk like imagine if we liberated the queer, disabled, trans, economically disenfranchised, muslim woman of color?  imagine all the forms of oppression that must be dismantled to liberate that person. we’ve got work to do y’all! to survivors of sexual assault: we see you. we hear you. we believe you. love y’all #metoo ✊🏽 #sundancefilmfestival (styled by @karenraphael tap for tags @ted_baker @kennethcole @asos @cosstores 🔥🙏🏽)

どういう経緯でロザリオを持っていたのかはさっぱり不明。
水彩画にするほど塗るところはなかったけど。
私のお気に入り。

buscad la belleza, es la única protesta que merece la pena en este asqueroso mundo (r. trecet)🍀 no me sigas si eres menor👦👧, más bien: si eres alumn@ mí@😱 si pinchas en este enlace y tiras hacia abajo un poquito, verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫
puedes leer artículos míos en diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: 
my novels arrive everywhere from

http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores de 18 años.🔞 you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults. ✌😘👍 todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 #margaritabokusumina #creativemind #artrevolutionary #spanishartist #masmujeresdeizquierdasypobresenlasaltasesferas #escritora #agencialiteraria #editorial #culturainquieta  #literaryagency #editor #publisher #peoplemagazine #visualcreations #agenteliterario #selfpublished #postpunk #femalewriter #metoo #blogger #weremember #video #powertothepeople #curator #morenonfascistsandpoorwomenathighestspheres  #harnessmagazine

text:
🧜🏼‍♀️ i loved the two previous books in this series, and while this final installment wasn’t my favorite of the three, i have to credit amanda lovelace @ladybookmad for the brutally honest, insanely courageous way she tackled this heavy subject matter and made it into something all at once beautiful and sad and hopeful and empowering. •
•
🧜🏼‍♀️i love her note at the end about the #metoo movement, and i also love that she included several of her fellow female poets’ work in her book- women empowering other women is a beautiful thing. •
•
🧜🏼‍♀️swipe to see some of my favorites from this one!
•
thank you @netgalley and @andrewsmcmeel for the free advance digital copy, all opinions are my own.

text:
many people think sexual abuse is always clear as day... violent rape attacks by aggressive strangers... but often times it starts off insidiously, silently, and with people you love and are supposed to trust. husbands, wives, fathers, grandfathers, step sisters, boyfriends, acquaintances, people you know, men and women... smiling, being kind, gentle. they may make you feel good despite you not wanting or refusing their advances. and what these people will do is manipulate you, guilt you, blame you, gaslight you, confuse you, and sometimes even threaten you to avoid accusations or punishment. it took me  almost 18 years to understand that i was being sexually abused by my now ex-husband. anyone can be a victim... children, adults, men and women, the elderly. and what i want to tell you, what is important that you need to know, that you must believe is... it was not your fault. it was never your fault. you did nothing to deserve it. please know that you are not alone. and if you need to talk... you are safe with me and i am here for you.❤️
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
buscad la belleza, es la única protesta que merece la pena en este asqueroso mundo (r. trecet)🍀 no me sigas si eres menor👦👧, más bien: si eres alumn@ mí@😱 si pinchas en este enlace y tiras hacia abajo un poquito, verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫
puedes leer artículos míos en diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: 
my novels arrive everywhere from

http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores de 18 años.🔞 you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults. ✌😘👍 todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 #margaritabokusumina #creativemind #artrevolutionary #spanishartist #masmujeresdeizquierdasypobresenlasaltasesferas #escritora #agencialiteraria #editorial #culturainquieta  #literaryagency #editor #publisher #peoplemagazine #visualcreations #agenteliterario #selfpublished #postpunk #femalewriter #metoo #blogger #weremember #video #powertothepeople #curator #morenonfascistsandpoorwomenathighestspheres  #harnessmagazine

text: i went to a few aa meetings a few years ago— one thing that stuck with me was that it was said that the age that you started to drink is the age that you got stuck at, that you stopped developing. when you sober up, you start back over at that age. i believe this applies to the point of my life when i really disconnected to my true self. i  finally cut off a narcissistically abusive relationship this past december and am looking at how i ended up in that situation. i am re-examining childhood traumas and how i progressively lost my inner voice over time. i can pin point shifts in my lifetime when i picked up habits and patterns that turned me away from love and i began to fill myself up with external things like my ego, work or relationships. i think i’m “restarting” as my pre-teen self. its been fun! i have began to listen to 90’s music from that time and do things that i have not done since then. i’m grateful that i’m feeling more connected to love and for this beautiful day. if i look like i want to sneeze in one of these pictures its because i do.

text:
easy. also for people saying abortions hurt babies:
research from the royal college of obstetricians and gynaecologists has found that the foetus cannot experience pain before 24 weeks and is kept in an unconscious state while in the womb.
the findings mean there is no scientific reason to reduce the abortion limit from the current 24 weeks, experts said.
campaigners had argued that the abortion limit for 'social reasons' should be reduced after emotive detailed scans of the foetus showed it fully formed, smiling, and making walking movements in the womb.
the reports were commissioned by the government to update the latest medical research last published in 1997.
it was found that connections in the brain are not fully formed until after 24 weeks meaning that the foetus is unable to feel pain and has no awareness.

text:
こんにちは、tieです！
*tieとは、神戸市垂水区多聞台で開かれている、多聞台地域国際交流の略語です

2019.1.26 
今月も開催する事が出来ました！

子どもたちと先生達と一緒に過ごす時間はとても幸せです。

この平和で貴重な時間は、どんな時も守られていかないといけないですね。そのためにはボーダーレスで柔軟な考えを持ち、常に前向きに行かないといけません。私自身がいつも会に参加して、襟を正される思いです。

子ども達って可愛いな〜😍と思い、癒されています。

そんな子ども達に、どうやったら英語が楽しく感じてもらえるか
また今日から次回の会まで考えていきます🗒日々、勉強です。

今月もご参加ありがとうございました❗️次回は2月23日に開催します！

どこの区の方でも参加出来ます！ぜひ、遊びに来てください。

参加ご希望の方は トップページ @english_tamondai  より、ご連絡いただけます。または、kehy_m@yahoo.co.jp  松尾までご連絡ください。

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
was angststörung in wirklichkeit ist, denn es ist mehr als sich nur “sorgen zu machen”.
angststörung ist das, was dir unruhige nächte beschert, wenn du dich hin- und her wälzt.
es ist das, dass dein gehirn nie in der lage ist, sich abzuschalten. es sind die gedanken, die du vor dem schlafengehen überdenkst und wenn all deine schlimmsten ängste in träumen und alpträumen wirklichkeit werden.
es ist, wenn du erschöpft aufstehst, obwohl dein tag gerade erst begonnen hat.
angststörung ist das lernen, wie man mit schlafentzug funktioniert.
es ist jede nachricht, die man sich fragt: „wie kann ich das richtig ausdrücken? 
angststörung ist die zeit, die du damit verbringst, auf eine antwort zu warten, während sich ein szenario in deinem kopf abspielt, was die menschen über dich denken könnten, oder ob sie wütend auf dich sind?
angststörung ist eine unbeantwortete nachricht, die dich von innen auffrisst, auch wenn man sich selbst sagt: „wahrscheinlich sind sie momentan zu beschäftigt oder sie antworten bestimmt später.“ es ist, jedes negative szenario, das du dir in deinem kopf ausmalen kannst.
die angststörung ist das warten. es fühlt sich fast immer so an, als würdest du warten. es sind die ungenauen schlüsse, die dein verstand zieht, und du hast keine andere wahl, als seiner destruktiven führung zu folgen.
angststörung ist das entschuldigen für dinge, die nicht einmal die worte „es tut mir leid“ erfordern.
angststörung ist der selbstzweifel und mangelndes vertrauen sowohl in dich selbst als auch in die menschen um dich herum. angststörung ist, dass man sich über alle und alles im klaren sein muss. so sehr, dass man erkennen kann, ob es eine veränderung in jemandem gibt, nur durch seinen tonfall oder seiner wortwahl... aber nach außen hin kann es niemand sehen.. _____________________________________________________

with alcohol when she met with him at a restaurant, but after they moved the meeting to his home to watch a film screening, tried to give her a massage. at a later meeting, the oscar-winning actress wrote weinstein propositioned her in a hotel restaurant. according to nyong’o, she met with weinstein for the second time — after having initially met him in 2011 at an awards ceremony in berlin while she was still in school at yale — when he asked her to attend a screening at his home after sharing lunch at a restaurant. when she arrived at the restaurant in westport, conn., where weinstein lived, nyong’o described weinstein ordering her a vodka soda and insisting that she drink it. “harvey told me that i needed to drink the vodka and diet soda. i informed him that i would not,” she wrote. “‘why not?’ i remember him asking. ‘because i don’t like vodka, and i don’t like diet soda, and i don’t like them together,’ i said. ‘you are going to drink that,’ he insisted. i smiled again and said that i wouldn’t. he gave up and called me stubborn. i said, ‘i know.'”about 15 minutes into the film, however, weinstein asked her to accompany him outside the room. “i protested that i wanted to finish the film first, but he insisted i go with him, laying down the law as though i too was one of his children. i did not want another back-and-forth in front of his kids, so i complied and left the room with him. i explained that i really wanted to see the film. he said we’d go back shortly. “harvey led me into a bedroom — his bedroom — and announced that he wanted to give me a massage. i thought he was joking at first. he was not. for the first time since i met him, i felt unsafe. i panicked a little and thought quickly to offer to give him one instead: it would allow me to be in control physically, to know exactly where his hands were at all times.” nyong’o wrote that after he removed his shirt and she began giving him a massage, he asked if he could remove his pants. #metoo text:
i have two huge passions in my life that i am so strongly pulled to embrace. 
one is doing all i can to save our planet and the other is to help young women by sharing my story.

so here goes........
in my early 20’s i was rapped. this was the worst experience of my life and led to deep depression. i felt so much shame around this that i wasn’t able to tell anyone not even family. 
a few years later i met my husband joshy. at this point i had completely bottled up what had happened.  when we were being intimate one night i lost it i was uncontrollably crying and i had to tell me what had happened. 
it took me about 10 years to even be able to tell my mum what had happened.

i am sharing this in the hope that it will help other young women who may have been through something similar.

over the years i have done so much work on myself around forgiveness and truely embracing my journey as it has shaped the women i am today.

after all the work i have done around this i had never forgiven myself, and i am the one that required the most forgiveness.

i have tears rolling down my face as i write this.

one of my favourite and most empowering releasing and forgiveness technique is what i call forgiveness letters.

this morning i wrote myself a forgiveness letter to release all shame that i have been carrying around with me and all the unnecessary blame that i have put on myself.

once i had finished i burnt the letter in the fire to release it to the universe. 
if someone is opening up to you about a horrible experience that happened to them it is your job just to listen.

i am here for any and all that want to talk. sharing your story can be healing in itself and you never know who it may help.

always choose compassion and kindness as you don’t always know what someone else has been through.

much love xx

text_retweet:
this goes for any kind of healing. #mentalhealth #sorrynotsorry
--
reposted from @end.sexualassault -  sorry for the inactivity but gosh life has been crazy! 
story time!!! so as lots of you know i am a survivor of sexual assault. i went through a trial and testified, won, and started to heal. but about a month ago i had to go back to court because he had appealed an objection the commonwealth had made and he won the appeal, because the judge ruled that i wouldn’t have to answer the question, but it was the wrong objection to make—she made a mistake. so he was granted another trial, and i have to make the choice of if i want to testify again or just not be involved. in the case that i didn’t testify he would be able to go free, only severing 3 of the 15 years he was convicted for. it’s a bit stressful lol. but if anything is has made me stronger, and i am hardheaded. he cannot get away with what he did to me, and no matter what happens again, i will not go down without a fight. 
so that’s why i haven’t been very active! anyways, healing isn’t linear at all, but it doesn’t mean you’re still not making progress.

text: i did a live on fb the other day and showed y'all how the transformation shirt fits now, here's the before and after pics so far. i was sleeved 12/11/17 @348lbs today i am 202, i'm 5'4.5" for reference.  i was a size 26/28 in tops and a 30 bottoms, i'm now a 10/12 tops and a 12 bottoms. this hasn't been easy but it's totally worth it!! i'm trying to stay consistent and go live a few times a week. feel free to friend request me, i try to post motivation and positivity always!! my hope is to inspire others and help you to #bethebestversionofyou  i have learned that we shouldn't compare ourselves to others, this is our journey and we all have different factors. i eat/drink high protein,  low carbs and i get in 100 grams of protein,  lots of water and vitamins. i use the opurity multivitamin bariatric optimized by @unjuryprotein and my blood work is great!! the vitamins are only $30 for 3 months and they have chewables and capsules.  i also love unjury rtd and the protein powders, there's several flavors including chicken soup and santa fe chili which are awesome savory options!! rich chocolate  is my favorite!! use my code lezette10 to save money. also if you have questions feel free to post or ask me. www.instagram.com/lezettechristinemua i post motivation,  body positivity, clothes, makeup, skincare, hair stuff, protein snacks and more. spread kindness like glitter and be nice to people lezettechristinemua #promua #makeupartistry #vsggirl #followmenow #fighter #survivor #methemoglobinemia #survivor #metoo #boudiourmua #nowbooking #nevertoolate #nevergiveup #againstallodds #aginginreverse #nottodaysatan #lovebodyandsol #proteinpacked #bariatricvitamins #beautifuldisaster #plussizenomore #bethechange #effyourbeautystandards

text:
devastador 🎥
el documental sobre michael jackson, “leaving neverland”, acaba de estrenarse durante el festival de cine de sundance y ha causado un gran impacto entre los espectadores.

el documental de cuatro horas es una crónica de las denuncias de abuso infantil contra el cantante, centrándose en los testimonios de wade robson y james safechuck. los dos hombres, ahora en sus treintas, describieron su relación con michael a partir de los siete y los diez años de edad y presentaron fotos personales, mensajes de audio y notas.

durante la proyección, el editor de daily beast, kevin fallon, escribió: “independientemente de lo que pensabas que sabías o no sabías, el contenido de esto es más perturbador de lo que puedes imaginar". variety agregó: “en “leaving neverland”, el testimonio de robson y safechuck es abrumadoramente poderoso y convincente. y una razón por la que es más poderoso que cualquier otra cosa que hayamos encontrado anteriormente sobre el tema... es que los dos no solo describen las actividades sexuales a las que jackson los sometió (sexo oral, masturbación mutua, visualización de pornografía). describen, con abundantes detalles articulados y profundamente emocionales, cómo se produjo el abuso en el contexto de lo que parecía (para ellos) una relación de calidez y confianza hipnótica”. el periodista gerrick d. kennedy lo describe como: “doloroso. brutalmente perturbador. desencadenante. mi corazón está increíblemente roto. lo lamento. esto duele mucho”. mientras que mara reinstein, crítica de cine de us weekly dijo: “me siento enferma del estómago luego de ver la primera parte de leaving neverland. los testigos y víctimas del abuso sexual de michael jackson parecen muy creíbles. es tan sexualmente explícito que hay terapeutas en el lobby”. 📌 “leaving neverland” será transmitida por hbo y channel 4 de gran bretaña.
.
.
.
.
.
#michaeljackson #leavingneverland #sundancefilmfestival #sundance #documentary #metoo #timesup #movienews #movie #film #pinkpresspe

text:
*** mental health rant t/w sexual assault *** haven’t posted about this in a while and wasn’t going to today but i know it helps some of you when i’m open about this. also here a photo from after i got rained on yesterday and wasted time in the h&m changing rooms because i didn’t want to be around people anymore 🙃🙃 i’m having a really bad depressed day today ☹️ i feel hopeless, sad, stressed, afraid and just generally unsure of everything. i want to cry but my body won’t let me which honestly fucking makes things worse. if you’ve been following me for a while you’ll know i struggle from depression & anxiety due to a number of reasons, including being sexually assaulted by 3 different men. i shared my story last march, it’s down my page if you want to read it & i’ll post it in my story. i know it helped me to read stories from other survivors. 
some days it really hits harder and i wish i knew how to fix it but i can’t and that’s just the way life is. it can never be undone all i can do is learn to live with it and that seems really unfair. i go through periods of feeling happy with how far i’ve come and then i feel like i’m right back where i started again. mixed with other things happening in my life it’s just making for a tough time. 
it’s kinda hard to get my thoughts out on to this post but it’s worth a try, sorry if it doesn’t really make sense. 
when you are a sexual assault survivor you are faced with reminders every day and you’re also faced with the realities of how unfair the system is and the overall ignorance that still surrounds this issue. it’s hard. don’t get me wrong i know i have come a long way. i know i’ve gained strength and i’m very proud of myself for using my voice to fight against the ignorance but some days i just can’t do it. 
to everyone who can relate to this, you aren’t alone. i’m with you and we’re fighting this battle together. i love you all and once again, it’s not and never was your fault. 
i’m going to try to turn off my brain for a while and hope that i feel stronger later. thanks for taking the time to read this, if you did. 💗
#metoo #ibelieveher
name: Erika Marie | Edinburgh Makeup

text: 👉🏾👉🏾 terry crews and d.l. hughley engaged in a virtual disagreement about how sexual assault should be handled by men, specifically those of a brawny build. the brooklyn nine-nine star addressed the comments hughley made about him during an interview he gave in august 2018. hughley had suggested that physical violence should have been used to fend off the unwarranted sexual contact crews' claimed to have experienced at the hands of a prominent film executive the previous year. earlier today, crews asked the comedian to further his thoughts on the subject. “you told the world ‘god gave me muscles so i could say no,'” crews tweeted. “are you implying i ‘wanted’ to be sexually assaulted? i’m listening, sir.” hughley responded by referring crews back to the interview by saying, “you saw the video!” to which crews responded, “sir you said i should have pushed him back, or restrained him and i did all those things… but you act like i didn’t. were you there?” hughley doubled down on his claim that proposed a violent rebuttal in the incident. “that’s different than slapping the s–t outta him,” he offered. this led to crews asking, “so sir… if you truly feel that is a correct way to deal with toxic behavior… should i slap the s–t out of you?” “i have looked up to you my whole career as one of the funniest most talented people i’ve ever seen. i remember when i saw you warming up the crowd at fresh prince of bel air and i thought ‘this man is a genius.’ but now you are an example of when comedy turns to sarcasm and cynicism," crews continued. "and you find it extremely easy to get jokes at someone else expense. you mock my success, but all i ever did was support you.” he added other players to his critique: “you 50cent unclerush and tariqnasheed have decided my sexual assault was hilarious, whereas there are a whole generation of black women and men who don’t think it’s funny. abusers protect abusers but they mock survivors as well. when you see me, keep it moving.” according to the actor, black men were particularly critical of him during this time. #jusswaggtv #jstv #idjswagg #newmusic #convo #metoo #terrycrews #dlhughley #radio
name: Jus Swagg

text:
aftonbladet rapporterar i en artikel idag, att en intagen misstänks för våldtäkt på en kvinnlig präst 13/12-18.

citat från anstaltschefen i artikeln: ”när en sådan här incident inträffar ser man självklart över sina rutiner. men det är ofrånkomligt att saker kan hända när man jobbar med människor, även om vi alltid gör riskbedömningar på alla intagna.” ska man behöva räkna med att, i tjänsten, utsättas för våldtäkt? har riskbedömningen för våldtäkt brustit? vilket leder till att det alltså finns ett avsnitt som riskbedömer våldtäkt? om man i riskbedömningen hade bedömt risk för våldtäkt, hur hade man arbetat utifrån det då? eller är det en oerhört klumpig formulering av anstaltschefen? 
något svar på detta vore rimligt. ordval och formuleringar _ä r_ viktiga när det talas om sådant dassigt som behöver normbrytas och attitydförändras. man kan enkelt  påverka omedvetet där det letar sig in och slår rot, eller när den redan existerande. subtilt.

citat från anstaltschefen i aikeln: ”när en sådan här incident inträffar ser man självkla över sina rutiner. men det är ofrånkomligt att saker kan hända när man jobbar med människor, även om vi alltid gör riskbedömningar på alla intagna.” ska man behöva räkna med att, i tjänsten, utsättas för våldtäkt? har riskbedömningen för våldtäkt brustit? vilket leder till att det alltså finns ett avsnitt som riskbedömer våldtäkt? om man i riskbedömningen hade bedömt risk för våldtäkt, hur hade man arbetat utifrån det då? eller är det en oerhö klumpig formulering av anstaltschefen? 
något svar på detta vore rimligt. ordval och formuleringar _ä r_ viktiga när det talas om sådant dassigt som behöver normbrytas och attitydförändras. man kan enkelt  påverka omedvetet där det letar sig in och slår rot, eller när den redan existerande. subtilt.

text:
from our january issue, @jessie_duffy’s dark meat series looks at how the front-of-house needs to loosen its stranglehold on the gratuity.

there’s little chance the food industry, notorious for low profit margins and intense labour demands, would wind up in a position to pay all of staff on par with a thriving server. not only that, tipping culture has vastly distorted the wage structure of the service class and skewed the public’s perception of value when it comes to hospitality. it keeps the chasm between the back and front of house widening, where it’s getting harder and harder to ignore that herd of well-heeled elephants stomping around the dining room, especially if you're watching from your perch in the kitchen.

considering an industry shake-up is already well underway — with the breakdown of the kitchen brigade; the #metoo scandals launching women to the front of the line; the deafening warning bells of an ongoing mental health and substance abuse crisis — it seems now might be the perfect time to throw the entire service model onto the flames and let it burn along with the rest of our broken and inequitable system. does that mean that tipping culture is set to disappear? probably not. but it would behoove those of us in the front-of-house who benefit the most from that culture to start naming our privilege and question the disparities that our take-home reinforces. it’s time to evolve, and above all, to figure out how to share.
.
read “here’s a tip”, link in our bio. illustration by @hellachella.

text: #terrycrews and #dlhughley having a conversation on twitter. last year during the height of the #metoo movement terry shared a story of an incident in which a high powered hollywood executive groped him inappropriately. crews expressed feeling violated and also conflicted by the way that a black man particularly of his stature could be mischaracterized in hollywood especially if he were to have reacted. i guess that hughley suggested that the proper response to having been assaulted by the executive was by slapping him in the face. crews explains his side. this is the ensuing conversation. i personally think that crews has the right to express disdain and also to be cognizant of the fact that not only in hollywood but in america black men are often painted and characterized in such a way by the court of public opinion that reacting violently poses a substantial set of problems- including people believing that his action was a reaction to being physically assaulted to begin with. what are your thoughts on this conversation? i don’t necessarily want to know what you would have done if it had been you- but i’d like to ask you to look at it subjectively from terry’s standpoint and give your perspective.
name: Black With No Chaser (BWNC)

text: a break from my usual poetry to talk about something very real. i’m sharing a very personal story. a story that so many people in my life will hear for the first time. this was my hardest entry to write. this was one of the hardest things i’ve ever done at all. i had my husband by my side the entire time just to get through it. and i’m not asking for sympathy. i’m asking for people to take a step back and try to understand that there are so many other perspectives besides their own. listen to each other. you might learn something. link in bio.

text:
stark blir bok som inte lämnar någon oberörd.

patriarkatet av  lisa gummesson.

vilken kraft det låg bakom denna bok. känslor av medlidande, sorg och en urkraft av kvinnors rätt att få säga nej när det gäller det sexuella och rätten till sin kropp. att få kraft att höja sin röst.

tre kvinnor möts av ett gemensamt öde där det börjar med ett ytligt men en stark vänskap. rätten att göra sig hörda genom ett gemensamt mål att söka hämnd. 
målet med hämnden var att männen skulle erkänna sina brott men någonstans på vägen spårar det ur.. en bok som berörde mig djupt och innerligt. att man som kvinna skulle vara villig och ta emot vad som helst bara för man druckit lite vin, varför gör det till männens rätt att utöva sina sexuella fantasier bara för att kvinnan inte kan / vågar säga ifrån när det väl händer.  även tro att det är ett gemensamt beslut. varför har männen rätten på sin sida när det gäller sexuellt våld, psykisk misshandel eller vad det nu kan vara. vår kropp är vår kropp och vi har rätten att säga nej. nej är ett nej. blir så arg.
det måste bli ändring på detta!! tack till @ordberoendefrlag för att jag fick möjlighet att läsa denna starka bok. 
stort tack till @skrivlisa för en kraftfull och  en viktig bok som berörde mig djupt. fick fram alla möjliga känslor och de var inte snälla tankar. 
mitt betyg blir fullpott 5 📚 📚📚📚📚 av fem möjliga.
läs denna oerhört gripande bok, patriarkatet! 
#patriarkatet #kvinnokamp
#metoo #gripande #recension #recex #bokbloggare #tacksam #känslor #rekommenderar

.
.
.
.
.

.
.
.
.
.

text:
terry crews and d.l. hughley engaged in a virtual disagreement about how sexual assault should be handled by men, specifically those of a brawny build. the brooklyn nine-nine star addressed the comments hughley made about him during an interview he gave in august 2018. ————-
hughley had suggested that physical violence should have been used to fend off the unwarranted sexual contact crews’ claimed to have experienced at the hands of a prominent film executive the previous year. earlier today, crews asked the comedian to further his thoughts on the subject. “you told the world ‘god gave me muscles so i could say no,’” crews tweeted. “are you implying i ‘wanted’ to be sexually assaulted? i’m listening, sir.” hughley responded by referring crews back to the interview by saying, “you saw the video!” to which crews responded, “sir you said i should have pushed him back, or restrained him and i did all those things… but you act like i didn’t. were you there?” ——-
hughley doubled down on his claim that proposed a violent rebuttal in the incident. “that’s different than slapping the s–t outa him,” he offered. this led to crews asking, “so sir… if you truly feel that is a correct way to deal with toxic behavior… should i slap the s–t out of you?” “i have looked up to you my whole career as one of the funniest most talented people i’ve ever seen. i remember when i saw you warming up the crowd at fresh prince of bel air and i thought ‘this man is a genius.’ but now you are an example of when comedy turns to sarcasm and cynicism,” crews continued. “and you find it extremely easy to get jokes at someone else expense. you mock my success, but all i ever did was support you.” he added other players to his critique: “you @50cent @unclerush and @tariqnasheed have decided my sexual assault was hilarious, whereas there are a whole generation of black women and men who don’t think it’s funny. abusers protect abusers but they mock survivors as well. when you see me, keep it moving.” get the receipts along with video of hughley's original comments at www.itskenbarbie.com or swipe #dl #dlhughley #comedians #terrycrews #metoo #entertainment #entertainmentnews #gossip

text:
#холокост #metoo #сакс #фрейд #ложь #конфабуляция
#вилькомирский

со "светскими" книгами я не церемонюсь, люблю, когда они выглядят потрёпанными. читая электронную книгу и в сотый раз, все равно не оставляешь на ней никаких следов.
 загибаю страницы в интересных местах. загиб в "реке сознания" на деформированных воспоминаниях и конфабуляциях. аксиома: люди редко помнят все точно. при этом они искренне могут верить в совершенно ложные воспоминания. смотрел сегодня суд над полицаями, там свидетель говорил о том, что жертв укладывали во рву лицом в землю и стреляли им в затылок. а полицай говорил, что такого никогда не было, он расстреливал надо рвом.
 модные сейчас харрасмент - сторис без каких-либо материальных  прямых улик должны пропускаться не только через сито недоверия к конъюнктуре, но и через сито возможных конфабуляций. общественный интерес на такое не способен. журналисты не могут устоять. иногда держится суд.
ну и замечательнейшая история "биньямина вилькомирского", как раз соответствует дате. представьте: существовали авторы книг, выдававшие себя за людей выживших в холокосте! как минимум трое. и речь ни о славе и деньгах, а иногда о такой сумасшедшей попытке выдумать свою неудавшуюся жизнь заново...

text:
#interraciallovestory  #loveislovestory™🏳️‍🌈 + #climateaction gender #debate "eve n'god this female is not yet rated ™" opens  feb 1, 2019 for a one week run through feb 7, 2019.  the " #freshoffthegrid™ #handmade " new indie run, follows immediately after #thefavourite runs.
eve n'god this female is not yet rated ™  plays 3 shows a day, #dtla  @downtownindependent cinema :  251 s. main street, la  90012  ph. (213) 617- 1033 
the allegorical #avantgarde fairytale is described as “1 day in the epiphany of a 21st century girl, who kissed a girl ™ a lost+found virginity #fantasy bordering on polyamory ; a bittersweet romance in the key of rock n’ #soul ; an immersive  floating #scifi dream as global girl awakens to the legacy of herself.” the all-female crew production from actressauteur™  cali lili + her #sustainable #upcycled movie + music studio in #gentrification -torn venice beach canals with #oceanconservancy footage including a local octopus named "octavia" + other #sealife appearing unprompted 4 the lens during principal photography was made w 90% upcycled original costumes + sets #farmersmarket items for "garden of eve" set.
co-stars legendary indie spirits award nominee, iconic actor/musician #wingshauser as lead male role, doctor godard / aka "god" with cali lili as "eve," and candace burney as “lila." certified on imdb as “ #triplefrated ” meaning it was written, directed and produced by a woman, making it one of the first (maybe the first) narrative motion pictures made primarily by women . the project originated, in part, as a response to cali lili's own " #metoo " experiences promotion of “all female on-the-set crew” began pre-production as far back as 2011 likely setting the current trend - against all odds, weathering early discriminatory push-backs from various directions. #lesbiancinema #lgbtqmovie

text:
bom dia amigas (os) queridas (os)

hoje é mais um dia de agradece ao pai por mais um ano de vida!!
hoje faço 22 aninhos... (até que enfim né!?!)rsrs.. inicio esta mensagem agradecendo a deus pelo maravilhoso dom da vida, pela oportunidade que tenho todos os dias de ser uma pessoa, uma filha, uma amiga.... acredito, verdadeiramente, que cada aniversário é um novo ciclo que iniciamos. uma oportunidade extraordinária de escrevermos uma nova história. um novo tempo para vivermos intensamente tudo de bom que a vida nos proporciona

assim como as oportunidades perdidas, os beijos não dados e as palavras não ditas que no ano que passou ficaram, conheci gente nova, fiz coisas novas, ri tanto, chorei, cresci um pouco mais… aprendi com alguém e com alguma coisa e vivi… também vivi!!! esse será sempre o meu lema de vida: viver e tentar ser feliz…

então hoje,ao completar mais um ano de vida,devo agradecimentos a todos voces que fizeram parte do meu caminhar,do meu crescimento,das minhas descobertas, conquistas e vitórias.por todo apoio,todo carinho,toda compreensão.
eu os amo tanto,e sim,eu tenho a melhor família e amigos do mundo.
e agradecimentos especiais vão para minha amada mãe,que é a razão da minha alegria constante,o meu maior exemplo e paixão. 
#gratidão 😘🙏🏽🎁🎂🎈💕🙈

text:
sex education révolutionne la série pour ados, le sexe et les rapports hommes-femmes (je pense qu’elle peut aussi empêcher la banquise de fondre : à vérifier). dans cette série post #metoo signée laurie nunn à laquelle j’ai consacré un post (link in bio), tous les mecs ne sont pas obsédés par le sexe, l’homosexualité n’est pas taboue, la virginité des garçons n’est pas un problème, les filles ont des pulsions sexuelles qui ne font pas d’elles des traînées, les hommes ont des sentiments et les expriment, les femmes de 50 ans sont sexy et baisent (je répète : les femmes de 50 ans sont sexy et baisent, quelqu’un peut mettre à jour yann moix ?), le consentement est désirable… et non, ce n’est pas une série de science fiction : c’est l’avenir. // 🇺🇸 every single teenager from 13 to 93 yo should watch and learn from #sexeducation. 
#changemakers #asabutterfield #emmamackey

text:
#teavwatcherz - read article here via tmz: 9:00 am pt -- r. kelly's attorney steve greenberg tells us, "mr. kelly has not violated the law. certainly not the mann act. the story has flawed factual predicates. beyond that, we remain unaware of any investigation, anywhere." r. kelly allegedly arranged a coast-to-coast trip for azriel clary when she was underage, and the fbi is now looking into the trip to see if r. kelly committed a federal crime ... tmz has learned.

azriel, one of the women featured in "surviving r. kelly," was flown from palm springs to phoenix to orlando on may 25, 2015. she flew us airways, leaving cali at 6:57 am and eventually landing in florida at 4:09 pm.

a source connected to azriel's family tells us the flights were arranged by a woman who was r. kelly's assistant at the time.

here's why it's potentially a big deal. azriel was only 17 at that time and that means r. kelly could have violated the mann act -- the federal act that makes it illegal to transport a minor across state lines for purposes of sex, debauchery or prostitution.

we're told the fbi just learned about the flights within the last week. as we reported ... the fbi has also been in touch with joycelyn savage's father multiple times in the last 18 months -- so it's clear the feds are taking the r. kelly allegations seriously. 
r. kelly sources tell us the singer believes he did nothing wrong because he claims this signed note from azriel's mom, alice ... gave kelly's assistant consent to care for azriel. it's not a great defense, because you can see it's dated sept. 21, 2015 -- but azriel made the trip back in may 2015. however, we're told r. kelly's camp thinks the note shows her parents were generally willing to let azriel travel with him.

he might end up having to make that point in court. stay tuned.

text:
after i-- something written about two-three years ago. about the effect trauma often has on person. that disembodied feeling. that inability to face what you know is waiting. the need to retreat into yourself after something indescribable happens. 
but, there's always healing within the hurting. this is also a reminder that you are strong enough to get through it.

text: i’ve made many. i wish my grandma had told me hers. i wish my mom had told me hers. i wish i could have shared mine sooner... i would have done so many things differently if i’d known then what i know now. and believe me i understand that’s beyond cliche lol. thing is i’ve come to know a lot of those sayings passed down by word of mouth have come to pass in my life. it’s so weird! we have a collective knowledge of the truth but we hold back from telling our truths and the women after us are doomed to repeat them. i need the cycle to end with us. i might not be able to change the world today, but i can change mine today. so here goes from now on, i will only speak my truth to the ones who come after me. it’s not fair to let them fumble when i’m on the other side of the mountain they haven’t yet faced. much love, vu💜❤️

text:
alyssa milano may run for political office one day – variety
#
alyssa milano is an actress, activist, producer, and former singer, and the “charmed” star might add politician to her plate. when asked about a possible bid for political office at the blogher health conference in los angeles on friday, she said, “it’s something that i think about.” “it’s not much different than what i’m doing now,” said milano, who has played an important role in bringing the #metoo movement to hollywood. “i’d really love the staff. i’m doing this by myself now. i want that person where i’m like, ‘can you talk to me about immigration in a way that i don’t have to go through so much research?'” “i would love it in that respect, but i don’t even know what trajectory looks like. do i start on a state, local level? if anybody has any ideas, tweet me,” milano continued. “2028? maybe. it’s something that i think about, for sure.” milano also sounded off on issues related to #metoo, white privilege, and what to do about men who have sexually harassed or abused people but continue to find work. just yesterday, variety reported that “x-men” director bryan singer, despite facing new accusations of sexual assault and misconduct, remains attached to direct…

text:
in 2015 i gave a tedx talk
.
i poured my heart out to a worldwide audience of my story, an old narrative of the wounding of childhood sexual abuse.
.
i used to think being a ted speaker would be the highlight of my career but instead it marked an end of an era, where i hung my cowbow boots and quit separating all the facets of me.
.
since then i've been learning to integrate myself into my own uniqueness, like putting together a rose again from these petals.
.
i quit using the name i was known by (abigail eaton-masters - thats for another post) and surrendered to the name of my bloodline and ancestors: waters. .
i'm sharing today because i am still seeing people's stories emerging of sexual abuse and woundings. i used to think it was an epidemic and i was scared by the enormity of it.
.
.
but now? now i see that we are all purging the false sexual matrix programming. our sexual innocence has been deeply betrayed but through love we are all finding our way home. .
i witness your courage and your bravery brothers and sisters and i bow in humbleness to your rising 🙏🏻
.
you can search youtube for "what does resilience look like?" if you'd like to see my tedx talk

text:
the feds run another sweep on robert kelly.

azriel clary, one the women who’s family participated in lifetime’s surviving r. kelly docu-series, is a key part of the fbi’s latest probe into the singer’s illicit activities. the fbi obtained the transcript for a flight r. kelly arranged for azriel when she was still a minor: palm springs to phoenix to orlando on may 25, 2015, on a slingshot rout.

sources close to the situation have informed tmz that azriel’s three-way trip was arranged by a woman – believed to be one of r. kelly’s administrative assistants. clary was 17 years old at the time of the flight, putting r. kelly in direct violation of the mann act – which prohibits the illegal transportation of a minor across state lines, for the purpose of sex, debauchery or prostitution.

tmz says fbi officials learned of the flight arrangement within the past 7 days. as reported, the feds have been in contact with joycelyn savage’s father throughout the past 18 months. you might recall, joycelyn savage is suspected of being one of r. kelly’s longstanding “sex slaves,” even though by all accounts, she’s been spotted in the public eye without robert by her side.

in turn, r. kelly has provided an alibi for the flight arrangement, through an unspecified back channel. according to kelly, azriel’s parents consented to the trip in a signed letter, clearing the way for her “safe travel” without the presumption of “sex trafficking.” oh lordy..get the full details at www.itskenbarbie.com #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #trappedinthecloset #muterkelly #metoo #seemslikeyoureready #lifetime #lifetimetv #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

text:
here goes nothing. i think i’m bisexual. and when i say “i think” i mean i’m 90% sure. the other 10% is me thinking that it’s probably just a phase. the first time i realized this was when i told a really close friend of mine that i love her and it didn’t feel like the friendly i love you that i usually say. another thing that hit me was that i’ve never been in a relationship and i’m pretty sure that my “gayness” is the reason. but coming from a desi muslim family you can’t do anything about it. coming out is not an option because once that happens i bet i’ll be getting married the next day... not by choice. so i just lay in bed at night, imagining scenarios of me dating a girl and how i don’t have to worry about anything. sadly, it’s just imagination. so i stick to watching gay movies and trying to date straight guys.
•

text:
this year #lahootimelo2019 is dedicated to woman/girl with the theme “an ode to a liberated woman” & i tell you it’s not an easy move. at times i feel very alone & isolated and at times very powerful having many around, i know so well it’s very sensitive and possibly unmask many human faced demons though it’s never my intention but i with my heart just want to believe her & believe all the brave women/girls who stood up and break the cage of fear and silence, they suffered and are suffering the traumas given to them by the demon men and it’s made society. she needs to be heard, felt & she has to liberate herself from the stories, tales and taboos she grew up believing. the men who enslaved women has become slave himself too and a liberation of women will be liberation of men too. all the kind men must stood by the women and believe her against the evil men this is the simple intention i have with this year’s #lahootimelo. 
this festival will be full of music, dance and celebration i assure it will be more fun than ever before and i invite you all to come and witness the two days of lahooti melo 2019 on 9th 10th of feb at university of sindh, jamshoro. 
#metoo #ibelieveher #hearmetoo

more from ala midwinter in seattle! join us as our own bruce macintosh, director of programming, moderates the panel, "support your local girl gang", today sunday, 1/27 at 2:00 p.m. on the poptop stage. three authors discuss their debuts sprung from real women across three different american eras: mallory o’meara (lady from the black lagoon - @hanoversquarepress) uncovers monster designer and actor milicent patrick's career and restores her place in film history. deb spera (call your daughter home -  @harpercollinsus  #parkrowbook) tells of three women fighting gender, race, and class issues in the 1920s south. former cnn chief white house correspondent jessica yellin's debut (savage news – @harlequinbooks #mirabooks) speaks to the #metoo movement and the volatile broadcast news scene. we hope to see you there!

full panel details: http://ow.ly/rkzp30nt5t1

text:
“we were never taught about mutual pleasure”, says alissa anne jeun yi in “love songs”. for the second part of last night’s double bill @camdenpeoplestheatre she took us on a tuneful, sparkling, joy-destined rollercoaster⁣ mixing “get on the dance-floor music, rap and spoken word..”. this actually heart-breaking, one-woman show will sweep you up in an engaging intersectional feminist narrative with poetry, courageous ironic humour, adorable hand-crafted props and on-cue mood music - exploring a from-youth deep longing for love, romance and intimacy and consistently calls loudly for better #sexeducation which will equip everyone around sexual #consent / non-consent. i wanted to cheer when i heard her say that but i didn’t want to interrupt the show.⁣ i’m so glad this show exists and that i went to it.
⁣⁣
i was surprised to see so many guys (visibly “guy-presenting” people) in the audience.. a really positive thing as i feel extremely strongly about men hearing #metoo stories, leading to the possibility of addressing their complicity in misogyny, non-consent and hopefully taking the chance to positive influence their friends. i also liked the sense of gender-non conformity arising from alissa anne jeun yi’s choice audience participants to represent the male love interests (which i think is a really interesting way of reclaiming emotional space). ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
as someone with friends identifying as asexual (aka ace) who struggle to find acceptance and visibility, i would love to add that asexuality *is a real thing!* it does surprise people due to its lack of visibility in a socio-cultural environment where sexuality is the norm. ⁣⁣from what i understand, aceness can manifest at times during people’s lives or be a feature, and it is also a spectrum!
⁣⁣
when booking for this show, i had not noticed the content note “contains reference to sexual violence” however i did notice it before the show, which was useful. i agree with the age rating of 16+. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#fabulous #funny #comedy #britishchinese #drama #dualheritage #identity #theatre #womenwriters #intersectionalfeminism #lovesongsshow #can2019 @chineseartsnow @alissa_ajy
name: The Mollusc Dimension

text:
صُدم العالم بقصة مريضة حملت وولدت أثناء غيبوبتها التي استمرت سنوات في ولاية أريزونا الأمريكية.

وهذه المريضة مثال على محنة نساء معرّضات لاعتداء جنسي، وقد تكون جانبا جديدا لحركة #metoo التي تشير إلى أولئك الذين لا يستطيعون التحدث علانية عمن اعتدى عليهم.

وأنجبت الضحية، التي لم يعلن عن اسمها، طفلا في 29 ديسمبر/كانون الأول، أثناء وجودها في دار للرعاية الصحية تديره شركة هاسيندا ( ) حيث كانت تعيش في حالة غيبوبة لأكثر من عقد من الزمن.

واتهم الممرض، ناثان ساذرلاند، 36 سنة، ويعمل هناك، بارتكابه اعتداء جنسيا والاعتداء على شخص بالغ في موقع ضعف.

وقال موظفون في المنشأة إنهم لم يدركوا أنها حامل حتى بدأت مرحلة المخاض.

وقدم الممرض ساذرلاند عينة من الحمض النووي بموجب أمر من المحكمة، وأظهرت نتيجة الاختبار أن حمضه النووي متوافق مع الطفل.

وللأسف، هذه ليست الحالة الأولى من العنف الجنسي ضد المرضى الإناث اللاتي يبقين لفترات طويلة في دور الرعاية الصحية وتنتهي بالحمل.

فقد سجلت حالات عدة مشابهة في أنحاء العالم بما في ذلك الأرجنتين والبرازيل ودبي وبريطانيا، فضلاً عن ثلاث حالات على الأقل في الولايات المتحدة.

image copyright google دار رعاية صحية تديره شركة هاسيندا (hacienda)
image caption دار رعاية صحية تديره شركة هاسيندا (hacienda)
إحدى هذه الحالات ارتكبت في مدينة نيويورك عام 1995 عندما اغتصب أحد المساعدين، كاثي كوب البالغة من العمر 29 عاماً، وتسبب ذلك في حملها. وكشف عن حمل المرأة، التي بقيت في غيبوبة لعدة سنوات، عندما كانت حاملا في شهرها الرابع.

ورفض أقاربها، وهم من الروم الكاثوليك، إجهاضها، فأكملت كاثي حمل الجنين حتى النهاية. توفيت كاثي عام 1997، قبل وقت قصير من عيد ميلاد الطفل الأول.

وحينها ادّعى مغتصبها، جون هوراس، في المحكمة أنه اعتقد أن الحمل قد "يوقظها"، وسجن لمدة 13 عاما.

أدت تلك القضية إلى تشريعات جديدة في ولاية نيويورك، وفرض إجراء تحققات من خلفية موظفي الرعاية المنزلية، فيما أصبح يعرف بـ "قانون كاثي". لكن لا يزال هناك نساء ضعيفات أكثر عرضة لجرائم العنف الجنسي في الولايات المتحدة.

image copyright getty images ممرضة
ضعيفات

أظهرت بيانات من وزارة العدل نشرتها محطة npr في يناير/كانون الثاني 2018 أن نسبة وقوع ذوي الإعاقة ضحايا للاغتصاب والاعتداء الجنسي تزيد بمقدار 4 أضعاف.

ويقول متحدث باسم منظمة "العدالة للإعاقة " وهي منظمة أمريكية غير حكومية: "أكثر من 80% من النساء ذوات الإعاقة سيتعرضن للاعتداء الجنسي في حياتهن". وعام 2015 وردت حالة أخرى من حالات الحمل أثناء الغيبوبة

أظهرت بيانات من وزارة العدل نشرتها محطة npr في يناير/كانون الثاني 2018 أن نسبة وقوع ذوي الإعاقة ضحايا للاغتصاب والاعتداء الجنسي تزيد بمقدار 4 أضعاف.

ويقول متحدث باسم منظمة "العدالة للإعاقة " وهي منظمة أمريكية غير حكومية: "أكثر من 80% من النساء ذوات الإعاقة سيتعرضن للاعتداء الجنسي في حياتهن". وعام 2015 وردت حالة أخرى من حالات الحمل أثناء الغيبوبة
stop_filter_tweet: صُدم العالم بقصة مريضة حملت وولدت أثناء غيبوبتها التي استمرت سنوات في ولاية أريزونا الأمريكية . وهذه المريضة مثال على محنة نساء معرّضات لاعتداء جنسي، وقد تكون جانبا جديدا لحركة التي تشير إلى أولئك الذين لا يستطيعون التحدث علانية عمن اعتدى عليهم . وأنجبت الضحية، التي لم يعلن عن اسمها، طفلا في 29 ديسمبر/كانون الأول، أثناء وجودها في دار للرعاية الصحية تديره شركة هاسيندا ( ) حيث كانت تعيش في حالة غيبوبة لأكثر من عقد من الزمن . واتهم الممرض، ناثان ساذرلاند، 36 سنة، ويعمل هناك، بارتكابه اعتداء جنسيا والاعتداء على شخص بالغ في موقع ضعف . وقال موظفون في المنشأة إنهم لم يدركوا أنها حامل حتى بدأت مرحلة المخاض . وقدم الممرض ساذرلاند عينة من الحمض النووي بموجب أمر من المحكمة، وأظهرت نتيجة الاختبار أن حمضه النووي متوافق مع الطفل . وللأسف، هذه ليست الحالة الأولى من العنف الجنسي ضد المرضى الإناث اللاتي يبقين لفترات طويلة في دور الرعاية الصحية وتنتهي بالحمل . فقد سجلت حالات عدة مشابهة في أنحاء العالم بما في ذلك الأرجنتين والبرازيل ودبي وبريطانيا، فضلاً عن ثلاث حالات على الأقل في الولايات المتحدة . image copyright google دار رعاية صحية تديره شركة هاسيندا ( hacienda ) image caption دار رعاية صحية تديره شركة هاسيندا ( hacienda ) إحدى هذه الحالات ارتكبت في مدينة نيويورك عام 1995 عندما اغتصب أحد المساعدين، كاثي كوب البالغة من العمر 29 عاماً، وتسبب ذلك في حملها . وكشف عن حمل المرأة، التي بقيت في غيبوبة لعدة سنوات، عندما كانت حاملا في شهرها الرابع . ورفض أقاربها، وهم من الروم الكاثوليك، إجهاضها، فأكملت كاثي حمل الجنين حتى النهاية . توفيت كاثي عام 1997، قبل وقت قصير من عيد ميلاد الطفل الأول . وحينها ادّعى مغتصبها، جون هوراس، في المحكمة أنه اعتقد أن الحمل قد `` يوقظها '' ، وسجن لمدة 13 عاما . أدت تلك القضية إلى تشريعات جديدة في ولاية نيويورك، وفرض إجراء تحققات من خلفية موظفي الرعاية المنزلية، فيما أصبح يعرف بـ `` قانون كاثي '' . لكن لا يزال هناك نساء ضعيفات أكثر عرضة لجرائم العنف الجنسي في الولايات المتحدة . image copyright getty images ممرضة ضعيفات أظهرت بيانات من وزارة العدل نشرتها محطة npr في يناير/كانون الثاني 2018 أن نسبة وقوع ذوي الإعاقة ضحايا للاغتصاب والاعتداء الجنسي تزيد بمقدار 4 أضعاف . ويقول متحدث باسم منظمة `` العدالة للإعاقة `` وهي منظمة أمريكية غير حكومية : `` أكثر من 80 % من النساء ذوات الإعاقة سيتعرضن للاعتداء الجنسي في حياتهن '' . وعام 2015 وردت حالة أخرى من حالات الحمل أثناء الغيبوبة

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

text:
#stylindoc alert : @azizaglass
・・・
“ever since i watched #survivingrkelly, i have reflected on my own experiences with sexual harassment in the workplace and academia. it is frustrating to know there is an infrastructure that protects (mainly) men  and demonizes the victims. it's not just r&b, hip hop, and rock & roll.
•
in 2017, a survey conducted by the veterinary information network (a large web based vet professional community) found that over 40% of responders had experienced and witnessed sexual harassment in the workplace. over 2,300 individuals participated.
•
veterinary medicine is considered a female dominated field yet the stats are the same as the national average if not higher. something needs to be done. it is not acceptable. i wish i had been mentored on how to handle these kinds of situations but unfortunately i had to learn on the fly. now i  know better. when i see something, i say something...and i keep a record of it. do your best to hold your employer accountable. you shouldn't need to "tough it out."
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#lifeasavet #metoo #changethenarrative “

“ever since i watched  i have reflected on my own experiences with sexual harassment in the workplace and academia. it is frustrating to know there is an infrastructure that protects (mainly) men  and demonizes the victims. it is not just r&b, hip hop, and rock & roll.
•
in 2017, a survey conducted by the veterinary information network (a large web based vet professional community) found that over 40% of responders had experienced and witnessed sexual harassment in the workplace. over 2,300 individuals paicipated.
•
veterinary medicine is considered a female dominated field yet the stats are the same as the national average if not higher. something needs to be done. it is not acceptable. i wish i had been mentored on how to handle these kinds of situations but unfounately i had to learn on the fly. now i  know better. when i see something, i say something...and i keep a record of it. do your best to hold your employer accountable. you should not need to "tough it out."
.

.

.
.
.
.
.
.
   “

text:
las calles son nuestras, las noches también.
las mujeres y las bicis estorbamos. estorbamos porque no somos la norma, porque somos “lo otro”, “lo diferente”, no encajamos.
la medicina mide valores a partir de un cuerpo masculino porque ese sí es la norma. el gobierno construye calles para los carros porque esos sí son la norma.
el patriarcado no quiere a las mujeres en la calle, autónomas, libres porque desequilibramos el estatus quo. el sistema carrocéntrico no quiere bicicletas en la calle porque desequilibramos el estatus quo.
el otro día, una querida amiga fue acosada y acorralada mientras iba en bicicleta. una vez un taxista me dijo “me da igual, si te atropello, tengo seguro”. otra amiga cuenta como le tocaron las nalgas en la bici y cuando protestó, le dispararon. está aquí para contarlo pero ejemplos sobran para demostrar que nuestra existencia es resistencia.
y somos muchas.. cada día más. nos cansamos, nos agotamos pero volvemos a salir. porque todas nos merecemos algo mejor. nuestras hijas, sobrinas, las mujeres de mañana se merecen algo mejor. queremos calles libres de acoso, vidas libres de violencia, calles donde tanto mujeres como bicis sean la norma.
lo queremos todo y no pararemos hasta tenerlo.
#mujeressinmiedo #mujeresenbici #futurasmujeressinmiedo #lacalleesnuestra #lasnochestambien #nadajustificalaviolenciacontralasmujeres #feminismo #feministmidwife #salud #ciclismofeminista #noeslanoche #noeslafalda #noeslabici #eselacosador #eselpatriarcado #metoo #loqueremostodo

text:
good morning.  so let me tell you about today.... usually i post on fb yesterday representing the day i left my old life but this year i decided to change it up.

i am not going to keep bringing up the day i left which was traumatic, rather i will focus on the next day, equally as traumatic, but a day that signifies a new life.

10 years ago today i began my new life.  i put the pots and pans i brought with me on the counter yesterday and told my oldest two kids... this is all i had (besides you guys and your brother) ten years ago.  they looked at me kind of crazy, especially knowing their rooms have dirty clothes and crap piled everywhere. 
the ability have those dirty clothes and crap piles represented the hard work put i’ve into life to be able to have them.  six jobs, 4 changes in where we live, lots of time away for business, raising three kids alone, missing a lot of things a long the way, but creating a lot of awesome memories as well.

at times 10 years has gone by excruciatingly slow, other times way too fast.  i am looking forward to seeing what the next ten years brings.

remember... taking that first step is hard but each step you build strength and you have the ability to create an amazing journey. #survivor #keepgoing #youcandoit #firststep #metoo #youareworthit #badasschicks #girlpower #smile #life #lifeistooshort #strength

text:
the volume of my voice is worthy of being shushed in the library, incapable of being lowered when i am trying to whisper, and manages to be heard over everyone in a crowded room.
i used to make the conscious effort to not talk as much as surrounded by people, i would try to silently observe the conversation because once i started talking i would be told to quiet down or let somebody else talk.
at those times that i would quiet my voice, i lost something. i lost the ability to express myself, i lost the ability to contribute, and i lost the ability to stay true to who i was.
at the same time, i gave other people the ability to evaluate what my quietness meant, i gave them the ability to assume my stance on the conversation, and i gave them the ability to believe my voice didn’t need to be heard.
when your voice gets quiet and you sit back, your voice loses its power and its importance. suddenly, you become a spectator instead of a participant. behind that decision to quiet down is another decision where your opinions, beliefs, contributions, emotions, and feelings get pushed to the side to prevent being seen as too eager, too vocal, or too interested in the sound of your own voice.
now without yelling, try not to worry about being shushed in a conversation, someone talking over you, or being the first voice that everyone hears. use your voice as a tool that allows you to connect, hold your own, and be present in conversations....

text:
wow y’all, it’s that time of year again! the boston area rape crisis center has announced the upcoming walk for change date as sunday, april 28, 2018 and our change for chantelle family cannot wait to walk to end sexual violence. my own liam neeson-worthy saga landed me on barcc’s doorstep with my caregiver nearly 2.5 years ago, and they have played a massive role in my recovery since. i’ve spent this last year healing, reflecting, and growing in my status as a survivor of sexual assault and attempted homicide. i’m looking forward to this walk date (our 3rd!!) as a true celebration of continued life, and i’m amped to raise funds for survivors like me who need them most! please, please consider walking with us this year, or toss a buck in the hat to help us achieve our $3,000 fundraising goal! i can’t believe we are actually here, year 3, or that i’ve actually made it. i’ve been pushing the progress harder than ever before over these last 6 months, especially with my traumatic brain injury, and i’m living for the strides being made! i understand the weight of my voice now more than ever before, and i’m getting even louder folks. whose excited? who will join me in supporting all survivors? *link in bio*
-
-
#supportallsurvivors #barcc #walkforchange #changeforchantelle #endsexualviolence #metoo #timesup #getloud #letsgoooo #barccwalk4change #healing #recovery #goodvibes #joinus #whataview #sunshinetime

text:
sometimes you have to let go of the picture of what you though life would be like and learn to find joy in the story you're living. ⠀
*⠀
*⠀
*⠀
⠀
guys, i struggle majorly with this. the picture in my head.. i thought i'd have the perfect job and making bank by now, i thought i'd own my dream house, heck i thought we'd have 2 kids by now.. but life works in it's own time. i have learn to accept that those things may not happen for a long time or at all. and i'm learning to be okay with it. i'm not there yet but i'm learning patience and learning to enjoy the journey through the struggles. ⠀

text:
hedy lamarr (born hedwig eva maria kiesler, november 9, 1914 – january 19, 2000) was an austrian-born american film actress and inventor.
after a brief early film career in czechoslovakia, including the controversial ecstasy (1933), she fled from her husband, a wealthy austrian ammunition manufacturer, and secretly moved to paris.
traveling to london, she met metro-goldwyn-mayer studio head louis b. mayer, who offered her a movie contract in hollywood.
she became a film star with her performance in algiers (1938).
her mgm films include lady of the tropics (1939), boom town (1940), h.m. pulham, esq. (1941), and white cargo (1942).
her greatest success was as delilah in cecil b. demille's samson and delilah (1949).
she also acted on television before the release of her final film, the female animal (1958).
she was honored with a star on the hollywood walk of fame in 1960.
at the beginning of world war ii, she and composer george antheil developed a radio guidance system for allied torpedoes that used spread spectrum and frequency hopping technology to defeat the threat of jamming by the axis powers.
although the us navy did not adopt the technology until the 1960s, the principles of their work are incorporated into bluetooth technology and are similar to methods used in legacy versions of cdma and wi-fi.
this work led to their induction into the national inventors hall of fame in 2014.
