text:
sound on 🙏🏽
.
here’s a very raw video i took at around 16,500 ft altitude while trekking to everest base camp in the himalaya mountains.
.
i had been trekking and navigating solo for days at this point. it was hard to breathe but thankfully i had no symptoms of altitude sickness, just a slight cold from the dust and dry cold air.
.
i don’t know why this particular mountain impacted me so much. it’s mt tabuche. and when i walked by i burst into tears. it was hard to cry at this altitude so i tried to hold it in but knew i had to make this video for myself. and today i wanted to share it with you.
.
2018 was very hard for me due to dealing with the trauma and aftermath of a sexual assault in 2017. panic. anxiety. ptsd. insomnia. depression. these all became my unwanted best friends and shook me to the core. i’ve been in therapy for 10 months now and go every single week. it helped me manage the severe lows that scared me and even those close to me a lot. i’ve never felt that low. that dark. that “place” where you literally didn’t know if you could go on. it was heavy and lonely.
.
through therapy, close friendships, family support and many many other healing techniques i finally got to the place in this video. it was this insane moment of:
this is what we’ve been working toward!
.
i don’t know why it was this mountain that healed my soul completely. but it did. i found forgiveness and resolve and peace right here. i remembered what feeling “alive” felt like.
.
so my message today to you is keep on fighting. i know some of you out there are dealing with this darkness and maybe everyone in your life thinks you are just “fine”. you.are.not.alone. i’ve been there. keep fighting. even if it is from your bed in the dark. keep breathing. keep being alive. because one day out of nowhere you’ll see something that is going to remind you why you fought when you felt like giving up. i promise you this.
.
and when you feel this moment, you will feel alive again. the darkness will fade to the new light in your soul. you will feel alive again. light and love always win. it may be months or years. just promise me you’ll keep fighting. the light always comes 🏔 #metoo

text:
anxiety
the body does not show it but the mind feels it. no one sees it externally and thus no one doubts it, no one steps up to help. you carry your agitated heart around hoping one day this feeling will escape your system, it doesn’t.
h e a l i n g - pour love into this feeling. ask yourself how you love yourself when you feel anxious. acknowledging all your emotions including the anxious thoughts is in itself a way to give power to the feeling.
#journeytolight
📷: @govindgopinath

text:
thru the years i've whittled down my dvd collection to only my top 10 faves, and  @tylerperry 's "diary of a mad black woman" is definitely one of them. this movie will have you laughing, crying, moved, and thinking. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this line that the amazing cicely tyson gives was so powerful to me when i first heard it almost 15 years ago. however it was walking in the aftermath of being sexual assaulted 5 years ago that it became real in a whole new way. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in this scene in the movie, cicely tyson's daughter is talking to her mom about the pain and anger from her husband's abuse. cicely says to her, "you've got to forgive him. not for him, but for you." ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
she asks confused, "for me?"⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and cicely replies, "when some hurts you, they take power over you. when you don't forgive them, they keep the power."⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i know how hard the concept of forgiving someone who has deeply hurt you can sound. it isn't something to be rushed, and there are very important steps to take before, during, and after forgiving someone, but it is something that is eventually needed. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
humor oder #metoo?
.
es ist schon spannend, was für eine interessante kette von gedanken, bildern und gefühlen ein einziges piktogramm auslösen kann... so wie das beitragsmotiv, das ich heute früh in einem kleinen berliner café entdeckt habe.
.
kann und darf man über so ein motiv schmunzeln oder wäre das letztlich nur ein zeichen dafür, dass man den ernst und die notwendigkeit der #metoo-debatte nicht verstanden hat? hat humor überhaupt etwas in so einer diskussion verloren?
.
es ist eine zutiefst bedauerliche tatsache, dass viele männer (noch immer) äusserst fragwürdige gedanken und vorstellungen hegen, wenn es um das weibliche geschlecht geht. und viele dieser vorstellungen drehen sich um macht und besitz - macht über frauen und besitz von frauen. das prägt sich in unendlich vielen nuancen aus - sexuelle nötigung und übergriffe, konservative rollenbilder, ungleich verteilte berufliche und soziale chancen sowie unterschiedliche bezahlung für gleiche leistung.
.
wo immer es um macht und besitz geht, ist die angst nicht weit - vor allem die verlustangst. und die ist bei den männern gerade sehr gross - genau wie die unsicherheit. das soll aber gar nichts entschuldigen, ganz gewiss nicht - ich verurteile aufs schärfste, was sich männer immer wieder herausnehmen und lebe selbst völlige gleichberechtigung und augenhöhe - in allen lebensbereichen, wo mann und frau (und alles dazwischen und ausserhalb davon) aufeinander treffen.
.
es ist gut - für uns alle, für die ganze gesellschaft -, dass diese alten muster und „privilegien“ endlich aufgebrochen und aufgelöst werden. und wenn diese entwicklung abgeschlossen ist, dann kann und darf man über das piktogramm auch wieder lachen. wenn klar ist, dass sich so eine szene nur dann ereignen kann, wenn sie von beiden seiten erwünscht ist - oder wenn der übergriffige zwei sekunden später ein blaues auge hat 😁.
.
wahrhaft starke menschen fördern alle anderen darin, ebenfalls stark zu werden und ihr volles potenzial leben zu können - völlig unabhängig vom geschlecht!
.
alles liebe, euch allen 💕
.

.

.
kann und darf man über so ein motiv schmunzeln oder wäre das letztlich nur ein zeichen dafür, dass man den ernst und die notwendigkeit der #metoo-debatte nicht verstanden hat? hat humor überhaupt etwas in so einer diskussion verloren?
.
es ist eine zutiefst bedauerliche tatsache, dass viele männer (noch immer) äusserst fragwürdige gedanken und vorstellungen hegen, wenn es um das weibliche geschlecht geht. und viele dieser vorstellungen drehen sich um macht und besitz - macht über frauen und besitz von frauen. das prägt sich in unendlich vielen nuancen aus - sexuelle nötigung und übergriffe, konservative rollenbilder, ungleich verteilte berufliche und soziale chancen sowie unterschiedliche bezahlung für gleiche leistung.
.

.

text:
when rca records dropped r. kelly from its artist roster a few days ago, those outraged by the mounting allegations against the american r&b star might justifiably have asked: “what took so long?”kelly had been associated for decades with rca records, a division of sony music entertainment, and been the subject of investigative reports, lawsuits and legal proceedings concerning sexual assault for nearly as long.as long ago as 1994, as reported by the washington post, kelly’s record company was tipped to the singer’s penchant for picking up underage girls after concerts by kelly’s own tour manager at the time.at best, the record industry consistently turned a blind eye to the charges swirling around kelly’s private life. at worst, it enabled him. the one incontrovertible truth is that the industry continued to profit from the music of an artist accused dozens of times of assaulting women and girls over a quarter of a century. -south china morning post

text:
what are/were you processing today? ❤️ #greatstory 💃
...
today’s energy with heightened opportunities was causing some internal conflict for me 🙄 the energy asks us to follow thru and enjoy a project that has our ‘heart in it’. for me that project is the book i’m writing. at the same time my stepchildren were staying with us this weekend. we don’t see them that much because they live with their mother in a city one hour drive from where we live. and of course they’re teens with their own lives so they’re quite busy with school and their own things 👍
...
the last 2 months i’ve been occupied mostly with the more ‘practical things’ to get business going but since last week i’ve been working on my book again, the final chapter. a pretty remarkable and intense process..
...
so what’s the conflict you might think? well, my mind was telling me to focus on the children while they’re here but the energy i was feeling asked me to focus on my book. conflict. now i already know i can be a cute star player when it comes to manipulating my feelings by ‘making up’ thoughts. thinking of what may or may not happen. which also is a good thing, but not when i let my thinking withhold me in following thru with what my heart desires..
...
so today i caught myself in the act while i was thinking that today is not a good day to work on my book because the kids were here and the energy in the house was somewhat restless. which it wasn’t: the restlessness was inside me..
...
to make a long story short: i just acknowledged the internal conflict i’m having. spoke up to let it out. wrote it down to raise my awareness. handed out some cash and sent the kids and their father out to go buy stuff downtown 😂 and now i’m working on my book with peace of mind. just like i’ve been doing these past days. finally 🙏😊 #everyonehappy
name: Yvonne | Philanthropist ❤️

text:
-
أوبرا وينفري
-
سبب قوي للكثير منا لكي يسعى لحلمه...
-
قوة الكلمة مختصرة في مقطع وَصَفَتْ به تحديات الماضي و الحاضر في العلاقة بين المرأة و الرجل و المشاحنات و عواقبها الأليمة في شتى النواحي الإنسانية
-
هي عاشت الألم و واصلت الأمل لحين حققت ما يشهده الملايين حول العالم. فأصبح إسمها لامعاً رغم أعداءها...
-
البعض يعتقد أن إنجاز ٢٥ سنة في تقديم برنامجها الخاص هو الحلم. و لكن هناك البعض الآخر من يظن أن قوة خِطابها دلالة (رمزية) إلى سَعْيِها للتّرشُّح للإنتاخابات الأمريكية القادمة!
-
لن أسالكم ماهي توقّعاتكم، بل أريد مشاعركم في هذا المقطع الذي استفز الحاضرين من نجوم #هوليوود لدرجة أن الكثير استمع، صفّق، دمعت عيناه، ثم وقف و صَفّق بحرارة، و غيرها من التعبيرات الكفيلة بالقول بأنها نجحت في توصيل رسالة المرأة - رسالة الإنسانية
-
#علي_السنان -
-
a strong reason for many seeking for their dreams...
-
the power of word is shortened in this clip which contains challenges combined between both; past & present, describing the behavior of the relation between women & men
-
she lived the pain & hope was along her heart until she made her dream a reality witnessed by millions around the world. her name became well-known even over the weak acts of her enemies
-
some may think that the completion of a 25-years show is her ultimate vision. in the other hand, many hopes (& perhaps dream) in her planning to run for next coming us presidential elections!
-
i ask you not to expect what is next for her, but to share your feelings in this touching clip which has made some many #hollywood starts applause, tear, stand-up & applause more, & other expressions which are worthy of saying that she made her message
-

text:
min datter kine♥️ stykket er fra facebooksiden til vi tror deg stiftelsen
#vitrordeg @vitrordeg #metoo 
vi ønsker kine hjertelig velkommen til teamet! hun vil lede kommunikasjon og tiltak i vi tror deg-stiftelsen.

kine ble i høst ferdig med en lang rettsprosess på fire runder, der eks-kjæresten ble dømt til 10 års fengsel for å ha utsatt henne for vold og voldtekter over en lang periode. en tidligere kjæreste har også blitt utsatt av samme gjerningsperson for denne grufulle torturen. dette endte med at gjerningspersonen fikk en samlet dom på 13 år. med dette soner gjerningspersonen en av norgeshistoriens lengste voldtektsdommer.

historien hennes har gitt sterke inntrykk, og blitt mye delt i media. det er ingen tvil om at hun har gjort en viktig jobb for samfunnet ved å stå i dette. nå ønsker hun å snu motgang til medgang, ved å bruke sin erfaring til å hjelpe andre gjennom vi tror deg-stiftelsen.

kine har et usedvanlig stort pågangsmot og er positiv som få. hun er engasjert, varm og omgjengelig. hun har også flere års erfaring med salg - og service, samt ledelse og personalansvar, noe som vil komme godt med.

kine var en av de aller første som tok kontakt med stiftelsen da den startet i januar 2017. hun har deltatt på en rekke tiltak som har blitt holdt i forbindelse med problematikken. hennes store engasjement for temaet har ført henne inn i stiftelsen.

stiftelsen ser frem til å dele denne reisen sammen med kine! ❤️ my daughter kine ♥ ️ 
in the autumn, kine finished a long trial of four rounds, where the ex girlfriend was sentenced to 10 years in prison for having subjected her to violence and rape over a long period. a former girlfriend has also been subjected to the same offender for this horrible torture. this ended with the perpetrator having a total judgment of 13 years. with this, the perpetrator is one of norway's longest rape judges.
her story has made a strong impression and has been widely shared in the media. there is no doubt that she has done an important job for the community by standing in this. now she wants to reverse adversity to success, using her experience to help others through we believe you foundation.
name: Inger Helen Pedersen 🇳🇴

text:
#twft52 week 4 – swipe for starter questions and my own response (also at link in profile).
@thewordforthis ✒🖤 the word for this is “accept.” ✒🖤 “do you want to taste (do you really need that?) something sweet, pulled fresh from the oven (damned if i do), damned if i don’t want just a moment of something rich and good before (too soon, you haven’t punished yourself enough) it burned, the promise of cream, sugar searing my tongue.”
✒🖤 the pairing of accept/except, something for others to receive, not me. food i enjoyed, especially rich or sweet dishes, a trap: the focus of family events, yet if i chose wrong, selected less-than-lean, didn’t fill my dessert plate with fruit and just a token brownie, cookie, the tiniest confection on the platter. "yuh fat"; he’d spit it with contempt, yet still grabbing, demanding handfuls of the flesh he purported to find repulsive. barely chubby early on, just a girl, just not-skinny. if i found the willpower to restrict (i never did, it was always found for me), if i made myself smaller, would i be worthy, my body mine? 
as i cycled into adult obesity, then watched the scale drop as i nursed my child (this one thing my body got right), praised as much for the sudden slenderness as for giving life, then rocketing higher still, until a combination of life’s evolutions and health problems ripped the pounds away again, dropping low enough (with a stop at acceptable, at my forever-wedding, unexpectedly svelte beneath the glittering smoky grey i’d chosen, as much the talk of those from before, as the undeniable triumph over life, in finding this unexpected joy, this second chance, that was what i wanted them to see) that doctors would express concern. 
i’m concerned too; i’ve gained back, i don’t look sick, yet i’ve tasted control (over her, over him?), the victory of too-small. it scares me; i abhor the undeserved praise, crave it. my fat was what gave him the right to touch me. when do i get to accept myself, or am i destined to feel like an exception?
name: The Word for This

text:
<warning> this is going to be a long read, dedicated first to all mothers, women, young girls and boys, struggling teenagers, anyone facing an identity crisis. you are beautiful. titik. if anyone tells you otherwise, delete them from your life (and instagram for that matter).
.
body-shaming has become such an unacceptable ugly part of our culture. nevertheless, it has been around for many years. what has changed now is the rudeness of people who just drop negative comments without thinking twice (and thinking in the first place). do you know how much struggle a person has been through? do you know how often a person feels “not enough” when looking into the mirror? .
.
i do! because i look into the mirror too. and every day i think, oh i wish i could change this and that, i wish i was 10kgs lighter, i wish my boobs were what they used to be before breastfeeding 🤪 we women struggle and we are already the biggest critics of ourselves. why not encourage each other instead of dishing out nasty comments? .
.
<storytime> i remember, allie was 3 months old, i went to a restaurant with her. one of the shareholders of the restaurant (and i am a regular at this place and know this guy for years) came over and looked at me and was like: oh seems like you are pregnant again! 💁🏻‍♀️ hello? i just gave birth. thanks for telling me i am fat not that i have enough to worry about on how to deal with life as a new mom 🤪 what did he gain from this comment? a splitsecond of amusement. what did it do to me? i doubted myself for days and feel like i am a 🐳. but today i laugh about it (and the guy) #byebyeidiot
.
.
in short, trust me. even without your mom-shaming inputs, we know that life is tough. we know that we want to have that sweet 🍑 back but it is sometimes not that easy. so why don’t you mom-shamers just zip it, or even better, try and be nice. it costs you nothing. and you can make someone so happy just by saying: you are beautiful. you are doing a great job. you are a great mom. .
.
and if you can’t say that then just say nothing at all and look into the mirror and think. are you really that flawless? ✌🏼 #stopbodyshaming

✅используйте порошки, гели предназначены только для детского белья
✅не пренебегайте полосканием, а лучшей сделайте это несколько раз!  что бы хорошо смыть остатки порошка
✅используйте кодниционеры для детского белья, они помогут сохранить игрушке первоначальный вид, нежность и пушистость🐰
✅не отжымайте игрушку в машинке на высоких оборотах(не более 600)
✅если стирали вручную, то лучше акуратно убрать лишнюю влагу с игрушки полотенцем
✅после стирки положите игрушку на горизонтальную поверхность до момента полного высыхания
🔻не сушите игрушки под прямыми солнечными лучами и на батареи, во избежание деформации!
.

.

text:
are you wanting your life to be different but it scares you?  do you feel frozen at the idea of changing? 
this has been my favorite quote for years. as i have let go of certain things, the meaning of this quote has changed for me.  what are you holding onto because you’ve been told, or once thought, it was how you had to live?  if you let go, the possibilities are endless! 
if the idea of change scares you, that is ok.  working with a coach can help you work through that fear, give you the support you need, and help you not self-sabotage 💜

text:
今日の朝
半年程前以来
無言電話がかかってきた
今回は番号非通知ではかかってこなかったけど
９月８日９時３０分に
非通知でかかってきた
無言電話と同じ電話越しの
テレビ番組の反響音のする部屋から
確実に加害者側だ
昔から集団強姦致死傷以来
定期的にかかってきてた人と
一緒であろうと思う
『何色のパンツはいてるの？』
とか
他の嫌がらせもこの人も絡んでるでしょう
かけ直したら
『しまった！』
とたぶん、関西弁。

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

devos’ proposal would only hold schools accountable for instances when its leadership was directly aware of sexual assault or harassment. schools would have an incentive to make the process of reporting sexual assault unnecessarily burdensome, complex, or traumatic — deterring students from coming forward, and limiting the cases which their leaders have notice of discrimination. in other words, schools could ignore best practices and create an environment where survivors were intimidated out of reporting sexual assault — then disclaim responsibility because they chilled reports of harassment. schools like michigan state, ohio state, and baylor would be let off the hook, even when lower level employees intentionally buried reports regarding serial perpetrators.⠀

text:
dear boys,

be a man they will say. 
let me tell you what this means.

be kind. be respectful. be open. learn to communicate. don’t be afraid to cry. don’t be afraid to be afraid. don’t lash out. don’t think being mean is cool. don’t think being cool is important. 
be open. don’t feel like you have to hold everything in. don’t think you have to go through all your problems alone. don’t act like everything is ok if everything is not ok. don’t hurt yourself. don’t hurt others.

be strong. but not just physically strong, be emotionally and spiritually strong. don’t worry about having a six pack and muscles that hold no purpose except to look a certain way. don’t focus solely on your exterior. don’t think you have to play sports that hurt your brain and your body to prove that you are strong. don’t get lost in sports. it’s ok to feel lost. ask for help.

be fluid. don’t think you have to prescribe to labels. don’t be afraid to hug your friends. don’t be afraid to give your dad a kiss on the check. don’t think that being gay makes you less than. don’t think showing love to others makes you weak. show love always. wear whatever colors you want. grow your hair long. wear makeup. express yourself fully without limitations. 
be polite. hold the door open for others. say please and thank you. remember to put the seat down. use your words to express how you feel, not your fists. use your brain. admit when you are wrong. speak up when you see something you don’t agree with. stand up for others. 
be humble. don’t be proud. don’t let pride guide you. don’t let your ego get in the way of making smart choices. be honored by second place. be honored you got to play at all. understand your privilege. use it with grace and compassion.

follow the law. don’t touch anyone who hasn’t given you permission. don’t speed. buckle your seatbelt. respect women’s bodies. respect other men’s bodies. respect your body. don’t drink and drive. don’t drink too much. remember your choices will have consequences. think before you act. think before you do anything. be smart.

boys we can no longer just be boys. men it’s time we stood up and said no more to other men. #enough #timesup #metoo

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
世の中には様々なレンズがある。
例えば常識というレンズ。大人というレンズ。男というレンズ。女というレンズ。それらのレンズを通して見れば、世界は歪んで見える。 「常識」というレンズを通すと、それまで自由で好きなことをして入られた場所でも、間違った行動に見える。
「男」というレンズを通すと、スカートを履いたり、化粧をしたりすることが「異常」に見えてしまう。
「女」というレンズを通すと、か弱さや、美しくいることが美徳に見える。

だが、これらのレンズは、あくまでの人工物だ。
誰かが勝手に世界を歪んで見せるために作り出したものだ。

でも、よく考えて欲しい。
そのレンズ。本当にこの世界に必要ですか？

text: #mentalhealthmemes #mentalhealthawareness i was having a very bad day yesterday and didn’t want to talk to anyone or see anyone. i just wanted to be alone, by myself so i could refresh my mind and soul. i’ve been for a nice long mindful swim and feel great 👍🏼 too often we get wrapped up in our personal life & social media and wanting to be the best we can. remembering that my life only got better sept 2016 which isn’t a long time. i’d suffered over 30 years of severe depression and that doesn’t change overnight. however in the years to follow i’ve created successful campaigns....helped many people regain their happiness and strength learning to embrace who they are worldwide and received 2 major awards (1 from 10 downing street pm theresa may) i appeared in several articles always with my positive mindset to help others. ‘pat on the back’. i sometimes feel let down by people around me who might see me as a threat to them 🤷🏼‍♀️ im a mother and grandmother first and foremost. it also makes me feel really sad that this social media life is allowing people to abuse the fact we are different although there is a fine line so be aware and don’t rush into becoming an influencer when a brand has no interest in your wellbeing (just a bit of advice) 🙈 my mindset was and is always to raise awareness and to let those know that i’m not in a competition to the finish line. so this year i’m looking after me 🙋🏼‍♀️i’m giving me a platform to continue rising and be that person i wanted to be when i was younger. i’m not going to allow trolls, haters or wannabes hold on to my swim tail or try to put me back to that horrible place. i’m a thriver and you better know it 😆don’t get me wrong. i’m all for empowering people which is what i will continue to do but i now know my self worth. thank you @maryrussell63 for being the best friend that i need. #lovetheskinyourein #bodydiversity #metoo #bodypositivity @thy.self @womenshealthmag @theempoweredwomanproject @theeverybodybeautystandard 🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️

several articles always with my positive mindset to help others. ‘pat on the back’. i sometimes feel let down by people around me who might see me as a threat to them 🤷🏼‍♀️ im a mother and grandmother first and foremost. it also makes me feel really sad that this social media life is allowing people to abuse the fact we are different although there is a fine line so be aware and don’t rush into becoming an influencer when a brand has no interest in your wellbeing (just a bit of advice) 🙈 my mindset was and is always to raise awareness and to let those know that i’m not in a competition to text:
we are excited to announce the theme for journo junction'19, "media and marginalities: issues and concerns".
the year 2018 had some of the major milestones of the decade.
the #metoo movement gave visibility to the sheer number of cases of sexual harrassment and assault. it was able to call out some prominent public figures who were involved in the crimes.
section 377 was revoked by the supreme court which decriminalized homosexuality. the trans bill contrastive denies fair opportunities to the lgbtq+ community.

the annual festival aims at revisiting these events and have a discussion around them.

.

text:
[magda]  wstał i podszedł do mnie. zaczął gładzić mnie po udzie. byłam w szoku, nie wiedziałam, jak zareagować. krzyknąć? uciec? obrócić to w żart? „no co, nie jest ci przyjemnie?” – spytał. „nie” – odpowiedziałam. „nie wiedziałem, że jesteś taka zimna”. „muszę już iść…” – wydukałam. tyle emocji było we mnie: strach, obrzydzenie, złość, ale stać mnie było tylko na to, żeby jak automat powiedzieć, że muszę iść. nie przyszło mi do głowy, żeby się komuś poskarżyć. to się zdarza – myślałam – to okropny, obleśny człowiek, jakich wielu na tym świecie. ale nie mam na to wpływu. najlepiej urwać z nim kontakt i zapomnieć o wszystkim.
*
[ania] siedziałam przodem do okna i deklamowałam wiersz. nie widziałam go, stał za mną, słyszałam, jak pije alkohol. „podaj mi rękę – powiedział w pewnym momencie. – ćwiczenie będzie polegało na tym, żebyś nie przerwała deklamacji, cokolwiek się stanie”. usłyszałam, jak rozpina rozporek, chwycił moją rękę i zaczął się nią dotykać. kiedy poczułam, co trzymam w dłoni, zrobiło mi się gorąco z przerażenia. miałam 13 lat i to był mój pierwszy kontakt z męskimi organami. próbowałam się odsunąć, ale trzymał mnie mocno. to było coś strasznego.
długo potem nie mogłam dojść do siebie. „zobacz, co teraz dzieje się w twojej głowie. to jest właśnie teatr” – mówił. a ja przecież nie wiedziałam, jak wygląda teatr.
*
przeczytajcie ten bulwersujący reportaż w wysokich obcasach. o tym, jak dyrektor teatru akademickiego: ryszard a., molestował kobiety i pozostawał bezkarny przez niemal 30 lat. każda z jego ofiar myślała, że jest jedyna i że nikt jej nie uwierzy, więc milczała. najmłodsza miała 13 lat.
ta historia jest jak studium przypadku „społeczny dowód słuszności”: widzisz, że dzieje się coś złego, ale nie reagujesz, bo inni nie reagują. np. <<[ryszard a.] jest znany z wulgarnego i seksistowskiego języka. potrafi powiedzieć do dziewczyny na castingu: „nie wiesz, jak się buzię otwiera? robiłaś kiedyś laskę facetowi?”. wszyscy reagują śmiechem.>>
ludzie, jest xxi wiek, nie dawajmy przyzwolenia na takie przekraczanie granic! w obronie swojej i innych – wtedy, gdy jesteśmy świadkami.
*
*
*
#metoo @wysokieobcasy.pl #terazczytam

*
[ania] siedziałam przodem do okna i deklamowałam wiersz. nie widziałam go, stał za mną, słyszałam, jak pije alkohol. „podaj mi rękę – powiedział w pewnym momencie. – ćwiczenie będzie polegało na tym, żebyś nie przerwała deklamacji, cokolwiek się stanie”. usłyszałam, jak rozpina rozporek, chwycił moją rękę i zaczął się nią dotykać. kiedy poczułam, co trzymam w dłoni, zrobiło mi się gorąco z przerażenia. miałam 13 lat i to był mój pierwszy kontakt z męskimi organami. próbowałam się odsunąć, ale trzymał mnie mocno. to było coś strasznego.
długo potem nie mogłam dojść do siebie. „zobacz, co teraz dzieje się w twojej głowie. to jest właśnie teatr” – mówił. a ja przecież nie wiedziałam, jak wygląda teatr.
*
przeczytajcie ten bulwersujący repoaż w wysokich obcasach. o tym, jak dyrektor teatru akademickiego: ryszard a., molestował kobiety i pozostawał bezkarny przez niemal 30 lat. każda z jego ofiar myślała, że jest jedyna i że nikt jej nie uwierzy, więc milczała. najmłodsza miała 13 lat.
ta historia jest jak studium przypadku „społeczny dowód słuszności”: widzisz, że dzieje się coś złego, ale nie reagujesz, bo inni nie reagują. np. <<[ryszard a.] jest zy z wulgarnego i seksistowskiego języka. potrafi powiedzieć do dziewczyny na castingu: „nie wiesz, jak się buzię otwiera? robiłaś kiedyś laskę facetowi?”. wszyscy reagują śmiechem.>>
ludzie, jest xxi wiek, nie dawajmy przyzwolenia na takie przekraczanie granic! w obronie swojej i innych – wtedy, gdy jesteśmy świadkami.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
podcasts - épisode 4
.
dernier dimanche de janvier, dernière session podcasts. alors évidemment, il y en a plein d'autres, chaque jour de nouveaux émergent et on en parlera petit à petit tout au long des mois qui arrivent.
.
en attendant, je vous laisse avec les 6 derniers, mais pas des moindres!
. 
1. @restezdansleflow_podcast
«le podcast sur la résilience d'une #metoo»
dispo: ausha, restez-dans-le-flow.me, deezer, itunes.

2. @yessspodcast
yesss revient sur les victoires de femmes ordinaires contre les injonctions et violences sexistes. tous les mois, avec @anaisbourdet, @zazem , @margaidq
dispo: ausha

3. @bampwr_podcast
«liberté. sororité. intrépidité. le podcast qui explore une thématique par mois avec une interview d’une personnalité féminine et un épisode dédié aux ressources (lectures, série, films..) sur le sujet.»
dispo: itunes, spotify, soundcloud

4. @tellementstellaire
un podcast spirituel qui explorer le langage des étoiles et qui aborde les thèmes de l'astrologie, les cycles lunaires et la divination par @maude.vallieres . 
dispo: youtube

5. «feminisme» @franceculture :
il ne s'agit pas d'un podcast, mais de plusieurs.. pour les découvrir on vous laisse taper «féminisme» sur france culture et faire votre choix..
dispo: franceculture.fr

6. @badasslepodcast :
«le podcast geek féminin et féministe animé par pia jacqmart, consacré aux figures de femmes dans la pop culture.»
dispo: soundcloud
.
la bise ! 🤜🏼🤛🏿💥
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. .
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said.
.
- the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
5 jaar later en verschillende dokters, psychologen, psychiaters en heel veel medicijnen verder, ga ik de komende 5 dagen naar psytrec in weert om mijn angsten onder ogen te zien en hard te werken aan het genezen van mijn ptss.

eerlijk gezegd had ik een tijd geleden alle hulpverlening afgezworen nadat ik een psycholoog kreeg waar ik absoluut geen klik mee had. zij stelde een verkeerde diagnose bij mij waardoor ik nooit behandeld ben waar ik in eerste instantie voor kwam. vanaf het moment dat ik daar stopte besloot ik dat ik er zelf wel bovenop kon komen, en dat lukte grotendeels ook wel door jaren te overleven. ik besloot te schrijven wat ik meegemaakt had en al snel volgde de publicatie van mijn verhaal op broadly. door alles naar boven te halen en alle lieve berichtjes en woorden die ik ontving, werd het mij emotioneel te zwaar. ik werd steeds angstiger en bozer en ik reageerde dit allemaal af op mezelf. zelfs mijn droombaan bij vice kon ik niet meer fatsoenlijk uitvoeren. ik voelde me toen echt een failure, ik moest hulp zoeken.

na een halfjaar op de wachtrij gestaan te hebben woon ik ondertussen in amsterdam samen met mijn kat en deels met daan, heb ik een vast contract en hou ik mij eindelijk aan mijn goede voornemens om elke dag te ontbijten ;-) en dit allemaal was nooit gelukt zonder de liefde, geduld en kracht van mijn lieve partner, mijn ouders, mijn vrienden, mijn manager en mijn collega's. you know who you are.

en nu ga ik een week offline ‪om 15 uur‬ per dag de confrontatie aan te gaan met mijn trauma. hopelijk kan ik hierna meer genieten van mijn leven en de dingen die ik heb. <3

dat wilde ik even delen. 
doei!

eerlijk gezegd had ik een tijd geleden alle hulpverlening afgezworen nadat ik een psycholoog kreeg waar ik absoluut geen klik mee had. zij stelde een verkeerde diagnose bij mij waardoor ik nooit behandeld ben waar ik in eerste instantie voor kwam. vanaf het moment dat ik daar stopte besloot ik dat ik er zelf wel bovenop kon komen, en dat lukte grotendeels ook wel door jaren te overleven. ik besloot te schrijven wat ik meegemaakt had en al snel volgde de publicatie van mijn verhaal op broadly. door alles naar boven te halen en alle lieve berichtjes en woorden die ik ontving, werd het mij emotioneel te zwaar. ik werd steeds angstiger en bozer en ik reageerde dit allemaal af op mezelf. zelfs mijn droombaan bij vice kon ik niet meer fatsoenlijk uitvoeren. ik voelde me toen echt een failure, ik moest hulp zoeken.

na een halfjaar op de wachtrij gestaan te hebben woon ik ondertussen in amsterdam samen met mijn kat en deels met daan, heb ik een vast contract en hou ik mij eindelijk aan mijn goede voornemens om elke dag te ontbijten ;-) en dit allemaal was nooit gelukt zonder de liefde, geduld en kracht van mijn lieve partner, mijn ouders, mijn vrienden, mijn manager en mijn collega's. you know who you are.

en nu ga ik een week offline ‪om 15 uur‬ per dag de confrontatie aan te gaan met mijn trauma. hopelijk kan ik hierna meer genieten van mijn leven en de dingen die ik heb. <3

dat wilde ik even delen. 
doei!

#ptss #trauma #metoo #bowie #cat #partner #love #therapy #psytrec #selfhelp #therapist #anxiety #medications #ptsd #girl #ragdoll

join us over a glass of fizz 🥂 and some of victors stunning sharing platters as we chat, dine and laugh, along with like-minded ladies and gents for another club elle event.⠀
⠀
we'll be offering networking with a difference so be sure to bring your business cards along and it may be an idea to organise a sitter! 👶🏼 club elle is an amazing opportunity to donate your toiletries and get involved with our fantastic raffle and of course, all proceeds going to vulnerable women living in refuges. ⠀
we'll have 15-minute phsycic love readings from the queen who is eleanor - £15 per reading. 🔮⠀
andrea crump is the fearless love coach, one of the leading love & relationship coaches in the uk and bbc relationship expert. 💏⠀
andrea is fantastically motivational and will have you and your relationship habits whipped into shape in no time. we’re so happy that she has agreed to be our guest speaker and to help whether married, single or it is complicated. ⠀
you’ll love her! ⠀
we’ll have fab tunes by our fave dj, di of @chickswithdecksuk and amazing raffle prizes. 🎟⠀
did we already mention, get a sitter! 👩‍👧‍👧 victors alderley edge is a stylish restaurant and bar set over 2 floors with an exclusive private dining room- perfect for your special occasion. located in the centre of the village on london road, victors has quickly become one of the main hubs of the village, serving brunch through to dinner daily.⠀

text:
national | oxford chooses ‘nari shakti’ as hindi word of 2018

details: the hindi word ‘nari shakti’ has been chosen as hindi word of 2018 by oxford dictionary. the initiative has been taken on saturday at the jaipur literature festival and also the subject of a panel discussion. “march 2018 recorded a large spike in the use of ”nari shakti” as discussion began around indian government’s nari shakti puraskar (women power award) given by the ministry of women and child development. ‘nari shakti’ got focussed attention both due to the efforts by the central government and hindi speakers with the aim of promoting inclusive development.” – said in a statement.

according to the oxford dictionaries, the supreme court’s rulings on triple talaq and entry of women into kerala’s sabarimala temple have added momentum to the idea of nari shakti. and the championing of the #metoo also helped to promote the hindi word in international platform. in 2017, oxford dictionaries had chosen ‘aadhar’ as the word of the year.

#narishakti #oxforddictionary #metoo #supremecourt #apexcourt #indianews #pratidintime

text:
💃supporting women to rise together💃

this is my mission!!
.
 i believe through sharing our stories, speaking our truth and practicing empathy with each other we create connection & resonance  and we realise..... we are not alone!! .
other women (other people) feel like we do. #metoo
.
our shame needs us to believe we are alone in our feelings of not good enough, not worthy, not enough, unlovable etc
.
we allow our own shame cycles (our wounds) to disconnect us through our harsh judgement of self and others, through our silence (not speaking our truth) and secrecy (not sharing our experiences) "empathy is the most powerful connecting and trust building tool that we have and it is a powerful antidote to shame" -brene brown
. 
by allowing ourselves to be vunerable, sharing our stories, speaking our truths and allowing ourselves to be witnessed by others... we will learn together to break and heal our shame cycle, so we can rise together and be the fullest expression of ourselves💃
.
i have created a space for women to feel seen and heard in speaking their truths and in the telling of their stories... .
where we will practice empathy and support each other to build each other up!! where we will take self responsibility for what is occuring in our lives. .
this group is for women who want to: .
💥explore thier own self expression .
💥get over fopo (fear of other people's opinions)
. 💥lean into their fear of speaking infront of an audience (facebook lives)
. 💥step into their power
. 💥meet other amazing like-minded women on a similar journey to you. .
if this sounds like something you are interested in 
drop "rising together" below... ... i will add you into the group
.

much love and gratitude to you 
erin-marie 😍

#womenrisingtogether
#brenebrownquotes
#selflove
#vulnerable
#empathy

text:
in sri lanka girls are told that wearing revealing clothes is "asking for it." as an adult i know that how a woman dresses or behaves is not an invitation for catcalling, groping, degradation or violence of any kind. being drunk is not an excuse for being disrespectful to women. not remembering what happened is not absolution either. 
realistically, i will ask my daughter to dress conservatively in certain areas and countries for her own safety; but i hope to also teach my son to be respectful towards women, because no woman is ever "asking" to be disrespected.
📸 by @rmaw83

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
why the gillette #metoo and lamb australia day ads are remarkable
#
gillette reveals new slogan, asks men to reject toxic masculinitycredit:gillettei remember all too well sitting in darkened projection rooms rolling my eyes as an advertising "creative", with delusions of cecil b. demille, and a star client would fist-punch the air and slap each others' backs after screening their latest toilet paper or fridge commercial.fast forward to 2019 and just as the internet changed the news game, so too has it disrupted the advertising industry, which today is more about social media campaigns and online content rather than maddening jingles and blockbuster 30-second television commercials featuring a cavalcade of celebrities.which makes the gillette and australian meat and livestock australia day lamb campaigns that much more remarkable. they have managed to break through the ever-fragmenting media landscape to generate debate among the masses, a much more challenging feat than ever before.within advertising, this is known as "earned media", when a television commercial becomes the topic of debate on breakfast television and twitter. in others words, indirectly promoting a brand for free.and to generate that attention, both campaigns have entered deliberately controversial waters, toying with such politically loaded topics as the #metoo movement for gillette, and australia's political and cultural inertia to promote lamb…
link: https://metoozoo.com/news/why-the-gillette-metoo-and-lamb-australia-day-ads-are-remarkable/

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner
